1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:17,851
A makeover project
for your most unhinged leftovers.

2
00:00:17,917 --> 00:00:21,221
The best chefs in Korea will
turn your fridge inside out.

3
00:00:21,287 --> 00:00:23,523
The classy cooking show has returned.

4
00:00:23,590 --> 00:00:26,693
<i>-Chef & My Fridge!</i>
<i>-My Fridge!</i>

5
00:00:28,194 --> 00:00:29,662
-Great to see you.
-Looking good.

6
00:00:29,729 --> 00:00:31,364
WELCOME TO ANOTHER EPISODE

7
00:00:31,431 --> 00:00:33,033
The popularity of our chefs

8
00:00:33,099 --> 00:00:35,435
is rising from day to day.

9
00:00:35,502 --> 00:00:36,836
-We've been riding the wave.
-True.

10
00:00:36,903 --> 00:00:39,706
This is especially the case
for Chef Jong-won.

11
00:00:39,773 --> 00:00:41,674
According to a recent survey,

12
00:00:41,741 --> 00:00:43,910
among non-drama performers

13
00:00:43,977 --> 00:00:46,246
on TV and streaming services,

14
00:00:46,312 --> 00:00:49,349
he reached number one in "buzzworthiness."

15
00:00:50,650 --> 00:00:52,085
1ST PLACE, 4TH WEEK OF DECEMBER, 2025

16
00:00:52,652 --> 00:00:53,753
Look at that.

17
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:55,522
He created more buzz than actors do.

18
00:00:55,588 --> 00:00:56,723
I'm jealous.

19
00:00:56,790 --> 00:00:58,258
-This is incredible.
-That's amazing.

20
00:00:58,324 --> 00:01:00,593
Will you share your thoughts with us?

21
00:01:00,660 --> 00:01:04,531
Thank you very much
for showing so much love and support.

22
00:01:04,597 --> 00:01:05,865
-All right.
-And he's humble.

23
00:01:05,932 --> 00:01:08,201
HUMBLE-HEARTED

24
00:01:08,268 --> 00:01:09,969
-But something is weird.
-What is it?

25
00:01:10,036 --> 00:01:11,905
Do you know who ranked second?

26
00:01:11,971 --> 00:01:13,540
Second place? Hyun-suk, probably.

27
00:01:13,606 --> 00:01:14,774
THE BEST CHEF OF THE SHOW?

28
00:01:14,841 --> 00:01:16,176
-It's unbelievable.
-Is it Sung-jun?

29
00:01:16,242 --> 00:01:17,277
-Is it me?
-Coming in second is

30
00:01:17,844 --> 00:01:18,678
Kim Poong.

31
00:01:18,745 --> 00:01:20,747
-Come on!
-Wait.

32
00:01:20,814 --> 00:01:22,882
2ND PLACE IN BUZZWORTHINESS, KIM POONG

33
00:01:22,949 --> 00:01:25,118
-Wait, is it trustworthy?
-It's losing credibility.

34
00:01:25,185 --> 00:01:27,787
-It just took an odd turn.
-That's why it's suspicious.

35
00:01:27,854 --> 00:01:29,556
What did you do to come in second?

36
00:01:29,622 --> 00:01:30,990
He wasn't in <i>Culinary Class Wars.</i>

37
00:01:31,057 --> 00:01:33,760
He didn't even participate

38
00:01:33,827 --> 00:01:37,630
in <i>Culinary Class Wars,</i>
yet he became the biggest beneficiary.

39
00:01:37,697 --> 00:01:38,898
I'm most jealous of him.

40
00:01:38,965 --> 00:01:41,134
But <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>
never reached out, right?

41
00:01:41,201 --> 00:01:42,569
-They probably have.
-Yes?

42
00:01:42,635 --> 00:01:44,804
-They definitely have.
-Well…

43
00:01:44,871 --> 00:01:46,539
No comment on that.

44
00:01:46,606 --> 00:01:47,674
A TOP SECRET

45
00:01:47,740 --> 00:01:48,842
So you turned it down?

46
00:01:48,908 --> 00:01:51,511
Please. I do not wish to comment on it.

47
00:01:51,578 --> 00:01:53,680
-Why is he so comical today?
-In that case,

48
00:01:53,746 --> 00:01:55,348
if you were to join <i>Culinary Class Wars 3,</i>

49
00:01:55,415 --> 00:01:56,950
should you be a white or a black spoon?

50
00:01:57,016 --> 00:01:59,752
I have no idea!
And why would I compete in such a show?

51
00:01:59,819 --> 00:02:01,187
It gets me thinking.

52
00:02:01,254 --> 00:02:04,557
-I mean, look at all the buzz you make.
-You came in second.

53
00:02:04,624 --> 00:02:05,925
-White spoon.
-Okay, Poong.

54
00:02:05,992 --> 00:02:07,727
-<i>Culinary Class Wars 3</i> it is.
-What are you saying?

55
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:08,962
Make sure they treat you well.

56
00:02:09,028 --> 00:02:11,431
-I'm not going to do it!
-Don't play the fool there.

57
00:02:11,498 --> 00:02:14,033
-Something else also became an issue.
-Yes?

58
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:18,805
He uploaded the screenshot of the ranking
on his social media account.

59
00:02:18,872 --> 00:02:21,174
He said Jong-won was the top,
followed by him.

60
00:02:21,241 --> 00:02:23,476
After that, Chef Jong-won

61
00:02:23,543 --> 00:02:26,846
<i>responded by saying something like,</i>
<i>"We did it" with a crying emoji.</i>

62
00:02:26,913 --> 00:02:28,915
-We did what?
-Well, actually,

63
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:31,050
under the name,
the ranking shows the program

64
00:02:31,117 --> 00:02:33,286
that the person caused the buzz from.

65
00:02:33,353 --> 00:02:37,157
<i>Both Poong and I made the list</i>
<i>thanks to </i>Chef & My Fridge,

66
00:02:37,223 --> 00:02:39,359
so I didn't mean just us two,
but everyone here.

67
00:02:39,425 --> 00:02:40,693
WE ALL DID IT TOGETHER

68
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:42,462
-Even us?
-All of us.

69
00:02:42,529 --> 00:02:43,930
On top of that,

70
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:45,598
Jong-won got listed twice in the top ten.

71
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:48,635
The second one was for his appearance
in <i>Culinary Class Wars,</i>

72
00:02:48,701 --> 00:02:51,304
whereas the first one
was with <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

73
00:02:51,371 --> 00:02:53,573
But Chef Hyun-suk had won the most stars.

74
00:02:53,907 --> 00:02:55,842
DID NOT MAKE THE BUZZ LIST

75
00:02:55,909 --> 00:02:57,510
Don't you remember the good old days?

76
00:02:57,577 --> 00:03:01,014
-You were once as popular as he is.
-He was a big shot back then.

77
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:04,551
<i>-You also once ruled the world.</i>
<i>-Well…</i>

78
00:03:04,617 --> 00:03:06,085
You're now a grandpa.

79
00:03:06,386 --> 00:03:07,687
TIME CAN BE CRUEL…

80
00:03:07,754 --> 00:03:09,722
-Many years have passed.
-Wait a second.

81
00:03:09,789 --> 00:03:11,558
Unlike the Jong-won and Poong duo,

82
00:03:11,624 --> 00:03:14,594
the white spoon pair, Sam and Ho-young,

83
00:03:14,661 --> 00:03:17,363
-apparently have become not so friendly.
-I heard that.

84
00:03:17,430 --> 00:03:20,400
There's a rumor that
they had a falling out, Sung-ju.

85
00:03:20,466 --> 00:03:22,168
-Here's the thing.
-What's going on?

86
00:03:22,235 --> 00:03:23,870
I watched <i>Culinary Class Wars,</i>

87
00:03:23,937 --> 00:03:25,738
and it felt like Chef Ho-young

88
00:03:25,805 --> 00:03:29,576
-was taking advantage of Chef Sam.
-Really?

89
00:03:29,642 --> 00:03:31,544
-Yes, he used their friendship.
-Why did he do that?

90
00:03:31,978 --> 00:03:33,479
DISAPPOINTED IN HIS MASTER

91
00:03:33,546 --> 00:03:36,749
He enticed Sam the Saint.

92
00:03:36,816 --> 00:03:39,752
-He did.
-Was it the one-on-one duel?

93
00:03:39,819 --> 00:03:40,653
You're right.

94
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:42,822
He eliminated Sam just like that

95
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:45,024
and moved on alone
as one of the top seven.

96
00:03:45,091 --> 00:03:47,393
-He did that?
-But wait…

97
00:03:47,460 --> 00:03:49,696
He did that after saying,
"All I need is Sam."

98
00:03:49,762 --> 00:03:50,797
-My gosh.
-No, listen.

99
00:03:50,863 --> 00:03:53,266
I had no idea
we'd have to duel each other.

100
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:57,270
So I held on to him
to move on to the next round together.

101
00:03:57,337 --> 00:03:58,771
But only I ended up surviving.

102
00:03:58,838 --> 00:03:59,806
AND TRAMPLED ON SAM

103
00:03:59,872 --> 00:04:02,709
I cried so much on the inside.

104
00:04:02,775 --> 00:04:04,410
Well, you're smiling on the outside.

105
00:04:04,477 --> 00:04:06,479
-What are you saying with a smile?
-Isn't he?

106
00:04:06,546 --> 00:04:08,915
What's going on?
Why are you saying that with a smile?

107
00:04:09,215 --> 00:04:10,683
A MAN WHO ISN'T OF HIS WORDS

108
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:13,653
He can't even hold the laughter.

109
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:15,255
He's mocking him. "Only I survived!"

110
00:04:15,321 --> 00:04:16,489
Look how happy he is.

111
00:04:16,556 --> 00:04:19,058
He's laughing because he knows
what he said didn't make sense.

112
00:04:19,125 --> 00:04:22,028
-It doesn't make sense.
-Why are you so happy?

113
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:24,697
One of you was bound to be eliminated
after the duel.

114
00:04:24,764 --> 00:04:28,034
It's my first time seeing
such a big smile on Ho-young.

115
00:04:28,601 --> 00:04:30,903
SHOWING A HUGE SMILE FOR MANY MINUTES

116
00:04:30,970 --> 00:04:33,373
-He's now in tears.
-He's crying.

117
00:04:33,439 --> 00:04:35,675
His face is red, but his cheeks are pale.

118
00:04:35,742 --> 00:04:38,845
-Right? Come on.
-Is that something to be so happy about?

119
00:04:38,911 --> 00:04:41,614
Yesterday, Sam called our production crew.

120
00:04:41,681 --> 00:04:42,615
What did he say?

121
00:04:42,682 --> 00:04:44,651
"When we shoot Chef & My Fridge,

122
00:04:44,717 --> 00:04:47,053
let me sit far away from Ho-young."

123
00:04:47,420 --> 00:04:48,788
CAUGHT

124
00:04:48,855 --> 00:04:52,859
He didn't want
to sit next to Ho-young for a while,

125
00:04:52,925 --> 00:04:55,028
because it'd be hard
to keep a straight face.

126
00:04:55,094 --> 00:04:58,097
Along with his request to our crew
for the seat change, he wanted this.

127
00:04:58,164 --> 00:05:00,133
No matter what happens today,

128
00:05:00,199 --> 00:05:01,267
who the guests are,

129
00:05:01,334 --> 00:05:03,036
and what the orders are,

130
00:05:03,102 --> 00:05:05,505
he demanded to fight against Ho-young.

131
00:05:06,906 --> 00:05:08,541
I JUST NEED TO FIGHT HO-YOUNG

132
00:05:08,608 --> 00:05:09,976
Does that sound okay?

133
00:05:10,043 --> 00:05:11,044
Honestly speaking,

134
00:05:11,110 --> 00:05:14,514
I haven't lost once against Sam
since last year, so…

135
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:16,115
3 ROUNDS, 3 LOSSES
IN THE 2025 SEASON

136
00:05:16,182 --> 00:05:17,450
Including <i>Culinary Class Wars.</i>

137
00:05:17,517 --> 00:05:19,285
You can always refuse.

138
00:05:19,352 --> 00:05:22,088
If he wants to fight me,
I shall fight him.

139
00:05:23,423 --> 00:05:26,326
I'll do it only if we aren't allowed
to help each other.

140
00:05:26,392 --> 00:05:27,827
No help allowed.

141
00:05:27,894 --> 00:05:29,562
In any case,

142
00:05:29,629 --> 00:05:34,734
we'll set up a round between you two,
no matter what the order is.

143
00:05:34,801 --> 00:05:38,338
As always, let us begin to ride the waves.

144
00:05:38,404 --> 00:05:40,640
Allow me to introduce our guests

145
00:05:40,707 --> 00:05:44,444
with excellent energy
to help us continue riding the waves.

146
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:45,545
Come on out!

147
00:05:47,814 --> 00:05:50,416
We present today's fridge owners!

148
00:05:50,483 --> 00:05:51,984
Please welcome the two cool ladies,

149
00:05:52,051 --> 00:05:55,588
actors Kim Young-ok and Park Jun-myun!

150
00:05:55,655 --> 00:05:56,956
-Hello.
-Welcome to the show.

151
00:05:57,323 --> 00:05:58,925
BOWING

152
00:05:58,991 --> 00:06:02,695
-Please meet everyone.
-Oh, my.

153
00:06:02,762 --> 00:06:04,230
-Hello.
-There are a few steps.

154
00:06:04,297 --> 00:06:05,198
Please be careful.

155
00:06:05,264 --> 00:06:06,165
SPRINGS UP

156
00:06:06,232 --> 00:06:09,202
-Oh, my.
-We're here with two special guests.

157
00:06:09,268 --> 00:06:10,603
-Right?
-Special? Hardly.

158
00:06:10,670 --> 00:06:12,071
She's now sitting on a throne.

159
00:06:12,138 --> 00:06:13,272
A throne?

160
00:06:13,339 --> 00:06:15,641
As of 2026,

161
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:17,243
she is 88 years old.

162
00:06:17,643 --> 00:06:18,911
AMAZED

163
00:06:18,978 --> 00:06:21,647
She's currently
the eldest active female actor.

164
00:06:21,714 --> 00:06:22,949
But it turns out…

165
00:06:25,051 --> 00:06:27,553
<i>that she still has a little girl inside</i>
<i>and keeps up with Gen Z.</i>

166
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:30,123
Please welcome actor Kim Young-ok!

167
00:06:31,057 --> 00:06:32,692
WELCOME TO THE SHOW

168
00:06:32,759 --> 00:06:33,960
I mean it

169
00:06:34,026 --> 00:06:36,729
when I say you all are amazing
for making these dishes.

170
00:06:36,796 --> 00:06:37,997
-Isn't that so?
-You're right.

171
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:40,032
And I often see him get cute.

172
00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:41,567
THE GUY WHO GETS CUTE

173
00:06:41,634 --> 00:06:44,303
And I saw the lady there dancing.

174
00:06:44,370 --> 00:06:45,972
THE DANCING LADY

175
00:06:46,038 --> 00:06:47,507
-And please tell us about her.
-Allow me.

176
00:06:47,573 --> 00:06:48,408
I was somewhere else.

177
00:06:48,474 --> 00:06:51,144
On screen, she's a seasoned actor
and a scene stealer.

178
00:06:51,210 --> 00:06:53,045
A SEASONED ACTOR AND A SCENE STEALER

179
00:06:53,813 --> 00:06:56,416
<i>In the kitchen, she's an expert cook</i>
<i>known as Seasoning Park.</i>

180
00:06:57,283 --> 00:06:58,918
Please welcome actor Park Jun-myun!

181
00:06:58,985 --> 00:07:01,120
-All right! Please welcome her.
-Hello.

182
00:07:01,687 --> 00:07:03,890
WELCOME

183
00:07:03,956 --> 00:07:05,792
I hear you watch our show
from time to time.

184
00:07:05,858 --> 00:07:07,727
It's one of my favorites.

185
00:07:07,794 --> 00:07:10,630
Also, recently…
My gosh. I really like you.

186
00:07:10,696 --> 00:07:12,465
GIGGLING

187
00:07:12,532 --> 00:07:14,233
-I see.
-He's the hottest.

188
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:16,369
The most buzzworthy.

189
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:18,671
-I've already lost my spirit.
-Is this a blind date?

190
00:07:18,738 --> 00:07:21,240
Are you also happy to meet the chefs?

191
00:07:21,307 --> 00:07:22,608
Honestly speaking,

192
00:07:22,675 --> 00:07:24,210
I have one bone to pick.

193
00:07:24,277 --> 00:07:26,746
Why do you make them cook
in such a short time?

194
00:07:26,813 --> 00:07:28,548
Why do you give them just 15 minutes?

195
00:07:28,614 --> 00:07:30,883
I feel anxious as I watch
on the edge of my seat.

196
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:34,187
How do you do it?
It was so shocking to see the time,

197
00:07:34,253 --> 00:07:36,656
so I thought,
"That just shaved years off their lives."

198
00:07:36,722 --> 00:07:37,690
WORRIED HEART

199
00:07:37,757 --> 00:07:40,226
-She's worried about your lifespan.
-It does, actually.

200
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:42,695
You're all so valuable, like treasure.

201
00:07:42,762 --> 00:07:46,299
Young-ok, you have an important reason
why you're visiting us here today.

202
00:07:46,365 --> 00:07:49,202
It looks like
you have something to promote!

203
00:07:49,268 --> 00:07:51,137
-Hmm?
-Please spend as much time as you need.

204
00:07:51,204 --> 00:07:52,872
-Really?
-Yes.

205
00:07:52,939 --> 00:07:56,042
Actually, it feels like
my last chance to do something like this.

206
00:07:56,108 --> 00:07:58,578
-I'm in a play,
-I see.

207
00:07:58,644 --> 00:08:00,213
and it's called <i>The Old Woman's Dream.</i>

208
00:08:00,279 --> 00:08:03,449
Do you accept an old woman like me
as a student?

209
00:08:03,883 --> 00:08:08,387
CHUN-AE, A GRANDMA AT AN ART ACADEMY
WHO WANTS TO DRAW HER FUNERAL PORTRAIT

210
00:08:08,454 --> 00:08:10,490
<i>It's a slice-of-life story,</i>

211
00:08:10,556 --> 00:08:12,692
<i>and I don't think you'll regret it.</i>

212
00:08:12,758 --> 00:08:15,728
-Wait, you brought some envelopes.
-Yes.

213
00:08:15,795 --> 00:08:17,997
A picture paints a thousand words,

214
00:08:18,064 --> 00:08:20,466
so I should promote this
with a chance for you to come watch.

215
00:08:20,933 --> 00:08:22,969
WOW

216
00:08:23,035 --> 00:08:24,604
You can ask for the best seats.

217
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:26,806
Oh, my. We should be getting
our own tickets.

218
00:08:26,873 --> 00:08:28,841
-Sure.
-I'll bring many more with me.

219
00:08:28,908 --> 00:08:31,210
-Thank you.
-Get up, everyone.

220
00:08:31,277 --> 00:08:32,411
RUSHING OVER

221
00:08:32,478 --> 00:08:34,046
It feels like I'm getting pocket money.

222
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:35,848
NEW YEAR'S POCKET MONEY VIBES

223
00:08:35,915 --> 00:08:38,117
-It feels like I'm getting pocket money.
-Line up.

224
00:08:38,184 --> 00:08:40,219
-Like New Year's pocket money.
-You're all so endearing.

225
00:08:40,286 --> 00:08:42,188
-Stop cutting the line.
-Don't cut the line.

226
00:08:42,255 --> 00:08:43,923
-They're feisty.
-He cut the line.

227
00:08:43,990 --> 00:08:45,558
I work myself to the bone.

228
00:08:46,325 --> 00:08:47,627
FLUSTERED

229
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:49,462
MY TURN

230
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:52,765
It must be wonderful to be so beautiful
and good at cooking too.

231
00:08:52,832 --> 00:08:55,434
-Do you have anything to say to me?
-Does everyone have one?

232
00:08:55,501 --> 00:08:58,437
It feels like any dish you serve
will taste homey.

233
00:08:59,405 --> 00:09:01,507
-Yes.
-Thank you, ma'am.

234
00:09:01,574 --> 00:09:03,709
-Thank you.
-I'll make sure I go.

235
00:09:03,776 --> 00:09:05,511
<i>The play will continue until March 22nd.</i>

236
00:09:05,578 --> 00:09:08,781
-All right.
-Let's go watch it.

237
00:09:08,848 --> 00:09:11,617
It looks like you two have made
a special connection.

238
00:09:11,684 --> 00:09:15,154
<i>Three years ago,</i>
<i>we sang together on another program</i>

239
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:17,590
<i>called</i> Hot Singers.

240
00:09:17,657 --> 00:09:21,127
Not every encounter leads to friendship,

241
00:09:21,193 --> 00:09:23,863
but this one did
because she's truly a great person.

242
00:09:23,930 --> 00:09:26,666
So through those occasions,
we've become closer as friends,

243
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:28,434
almost like family.

244
00:09:28,501 --> 00:09:30,603
Also, she makes mean kimchi,

245
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:32,038
and it's so amazing.

246
00:09:32,104 --> 00:09:34,740
-Her kimchi.
-I didn't know she could do that.

247
00:09:34,807 --> 00:09:38,578
-She's such an amazing cook.
-She is.

248
00:09:38,644 --> 00:09:44,317
Young-ok has recently gained popularity
as the Gen Z Granny.

249
00:09:44,383 --> 00:09:45,851
One of our chefs

250
00:09:45,918 --> 00:09:50,790
also has a deep respect
for your Gen Z sides.

251
00:09:50,856 --> 00:09:52,224
Chef Jong-won?

252
00:09:52,291 --> 00:09:53,859
-Hmm?
-Is that so?

253
00:09:53,926 --> 00:09:56,796
I recently watched your visit
to the popular hot pot joint.

254
00:09:56,862 --> 00:09:59,665
Many of my teammates
are also Millennials and Gen Zers,

255
00:09:59,732 --> 00:10:01,467
<i>so I went to the same joint with them,</i>

256
00:10:01,534 --> 00:10:03,769
and it was harder than it seemed
to dine there.

257
00:10:03,836 --> 00:10:07,073
But then I saw you
enjoying the experience more than I did.

258
00:10:07,139 --> 00:10:10,376
I had no idea what that place was,
so it was my first time there.

259
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:13,346
Recently, I had my chance to eat there,

260
00:10:13,412 --> 00:10:15,648
and it was so delicious.

261
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:18,050
FOUND A LIKING FOR HOT POT AT AGE 88

262
00:10:18,117 --> 00:10:21,220
We prepared a video
of that popular Gen Z hot pot place.

263
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:23,456
Let's find out what she did there.

264
00:10:23,923 --> 00:10:24,991
HEHEHEHE

265
00:10:25,057 --> 00:10:26,359
It's huge.

266
00:10:26,425 --> 00:10:27,493
So this is the place.

267
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:31,397
On that day, there were
no elderly people except for me.

268
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:32,798
Goodness.

269
00:10:32,865 --> 00:10:34,767
Gosh. This is so spicy.

270
00:10:35,835 --> 00:10:37,570
She did that spinning trick too.

271
00:10:37,637 --> 00:10:38,738
Hey!

272
00:10:38,804 --> 00:10:40,006
SUCCEEDS AFTER ONE TRY

273
00:10:40,072 --> 00:10:41,207
She's good at that.

274
00:10:41,841 --> 00:10:44,043
You have to watch that. The noodle dance.

275
00:10:44,577 --> 00:10:46,178
FLASHY TECHNIQUES

276
00:10:46,245 --> 00:10:47,079
EXTREMELY SATISFIED
LOL

277
00:10:47,246 --> 00:10:49,882
LASTLY, TANGHULU MUKBANG

278
00:10:49,949 --> 00:10:51,083
THE EXCITING FIRST BITE

279
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:52,485
-That was good.
-Strawberries.

280
00:10:52,551 --> 00:10:53,919
This is good.

281
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:55,788
I'm going to devour tanghulu.

282
00:10:56,555 --> 00:10:59,358
-That's amazing.
-I did all kinds of nonsense.

283
00:10:59,925 --> 00:11:00,960
MASTERED THE GEN Z DAY OUT

284
00:11:01,027 --> 00:11:02,795
-Wait, so…
-Goodness.

285
00:11:02,862 --> 00:11:04,697
Wasn't <i>tanghulu </i>a bit hard?

286
00:11:04,764 --> 00:11:05,998
It was, but my teeth are fine.

287
00:11:06,065 --> 00:11:07,199
I HAVE GOOD TEETH

288
00:11:07,266 --> 00:11:08,834
-She has good teeth.
-Yes.

289
00:11:08,901 --> 00:11:10,469
-You have good teeth.
-That too,

290
00:11:10,536 --> 00:11:12,905
but if that <i>tanghulu</i> wasn't hard,

291
00:11:12,972 --> 00:11:14,540
it can't be called <i>tanghulu.</i>

292
00:11:14,607 --> 00:11:16,609
It has to be crunchy on the outside

293
00:11:16,676 --> 00:11:18,310
-and soft on the inside.
-You're right.

294
00:11:18,377 --> 00:11:19,912
Back in her day,

295
00:11:19,979 --> 00:11:22,481
she had the old school hard candy,

296
00:11:22,548 --> 00:11:25,251
so someone who had that
must think <i>tanghulu</i> is a joke.

297
00:11:25,317 --> 00:11:28,087
Yes, I can still eat
the sugar-coated hard candy.

298
00:11:28,154 --> 00:11:30,423
-She has very healthy teeth.
-She does.

299
00:11:30,489 --> 00:11:32,058
Have you been there, Hyun-suk?

300
00:11:32,124 --> 00:11:33,559
I love that place.

301
00:11:33,626 --> 00:11:36,062
-I see.
-I even have a special sauce recipe.

302
00:11:36,128 --> 00:11:39,331
Since I'm a real old-timer,

303
00:11:39,398 --> 00:11:40,866
-I know--
-How are you an old-timer?

304
00:11:41,434 --> 00:11:42,835
DO YOU DARE TO SAY THAT BEFORE ME?

305
00:11:43,269 --> 00:11:45,738
MAKING THE ACTUAL ELDERLY WOMAN ANGRY

306
00:11:45,805 --> 00:11:47,707
-He'll have a grandson soon.
-How old are you?

307
00:11:47,773 --> 00:11:49,075
I'm 55 years old.

308
00:11:49,141 --> 00:11:50,943
You must've married young.

309
00:11:51,644 --> 00:11:53,612
And his daughter got married young.

310
00:11:53,679 --> 00:11:57,049
He still looks too young and firm,
so it's kind of odd.

311
00:11:58,317 --> 00:12:00,319
His grandson isn't even born, but he says

312
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:02,488
-he'll bring him up as a baseball player…
-Play baseball.

313
00:12:02,555 --> 00:12:04,123
…and whatnot.

314
00:12:04,190 --> 00:12:06,625
Just let him be.

315
00:12:06,692 --> 00:12:09,929
Later on, he may become
an excellent soccer player like Jung-hwan,

316
00:12:09,995 --> 00:12:14,166
even a renowned host just like Sung-ju,

317
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:16,368
-or a chef like you.
-Yes.

318
00:12:16,435 --> 00:12:18,504
-Just go with the flow.
-Go with the flow.

319
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:21,774
The grandpa doesn't have to step in
and try to mold his grandson.

320
00:12:22,174 --> 00:12:23,642
FINALLY, SOMEONE SAID IT

321
00:12:23,709 --> 00:12:25,311
-Wise words.
-He doesn't have to be a ball player.

322
00:12:25,377 --> 00:12:27,246
I was just trying to be funny…

323
00:12:27,313 --> 00:12:28,280
BACKS DOWN RIGHT AWAY

324
00:12:28,347 --> 00:12:30,282
She recently did a photo shoot

325
00:12:30,349 --> 00:12:32,952
-and had a dramatic makeover…
-I'm curious.

326
00:12:33,018 --> 00:12:34,587
…to show another side of her.

327
00:12:34,653 --> 00:12:35,921
-Gosh.
-Let's take a look.

328
00:12:36,422 --> 00:12:37,389
It's not dramatic.

329
00:12:37,456 --> 00:12:39,425
IT'S SO DRAMATIC

330
00:12:39,492 --> 00:12:41,494
-Like Queen Elizabeth.
-Queen Elizabeth.

331
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:42,828
-You're right.
-She resembles her.

332
00:12:42,895 --> 00:12:44,096
-That's so cool.
-She's the Queen.

333
00:12:44,163 --> 00:12:45,030
She's the Queen.

334
00:12:45,097 --> 00:12:46,699
-You seem so different.
-She is the Queen.

335
00:12:46,766 --> 00:12:50,002
They asked what I wanted to dress up as,
and it didn't take me a second to answer.

336
00:12:50,069 --> 00:12:52,671
"Make me a queen."

337
00:12:53,272 --> 00:12:54,607
"Make me a queen."

338
00:12:54,673 --> 00:12:56,609
So that's that.

339
00:12:56,675 --> 00:13:00,379
-A few of our chefs did photo shoots too.
-Many of them.

340
00:13:00,446 --> 00:13:01,580
-Yes.
-A photo shoot?

341
00:13:01,647 --> 00:13:04,517
-Let's see the pictures.
-Let's see it.

342
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:05,618
-Could it be?
-Someone did it.

343
00:13:06,285 --> 00:13:08,020
A PHOTO SHOOT WITH GOOD VIBES

344
00:13:08,087 --> 00:13:09,288
-No way.
-I'm jealous.

345
00:13:09,355 --> 00:13:11,123
-It was Chef Jong-won.
-That's so cool.

346
00:13:11,190 --> 00:13:12,525
-I'm jealous.
-He's like a K-pop idol.

347
00:13:12,591 --> 00:13:14,593
-His legs are unnecessarily long.
-Look at you.

348
00:13:14,660 --> 00:13:17,596
-He's like a celebrity among chefs.
-Goodness.

349
00:13:17,663 --> 00:13:19,298
I suddenly feel deprived.

350
00:13:19,365 --> 00:13:20,499
Look at that bad boy look.

351
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:23,068
STARE

352
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:25,104
You seem to love Jong-won's photo shoot.

353
00:13:25,171 --> 00:13:26,472
Yes, I love it.

354
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:29,842
-Would you like a copy?
-Yes, please.

355
00:13:29,909 --> 00:13:32,745
-May I have it signed?
-With the autograph, then.

356
00:13:32,812 --> 00:13:34,547
Didn't it feel awkward? Was it okay?

357
00:13:34,613 --> 00:13:36,282
-It was tough.
-Was it?

358
00:13:36,348 --> 00:13:38,417
I couldn't make the usual poses like this,

359
00:13:38,484 --> 00:13:41,353
so I had to do something like this.

360
00:13:41,420 --> 00:13:42,988
-He looks great.
-It was my first time.

361
00:13:43,055 --> 00:13:44,623
Are there any others?

362
00:13:45,858 --> 00:13:47,960
HEH, IT'S MY TURN

363
00:13:48,027 --> 00:13:49,962
-When did you take these?
-Who is that?

364
00:13:50,029 --> 00:13:51,163
Are these recent?

365
00:13:51,230 --> 00:13:53,032
No, it must've been last year.

366
00:13:53,098 --> 00:13:54,200
The leftmost one means,

367
00:13:54,266 --> 00:13:56,535
"I want everything on the menu
from here to here."

368
00:13:56,602 --> 00:13:57,937
MENU_POV.JPG

369
00:13:58,003 --> 00:13:59,305
So these were all approved?

370
00:13:59,371 --> 00:14:00,306
THAT'S WHAT I DO

371
00:14:00,372 --> 00:14:01,740
Take a closer look.

372
00:14:01,807 --> 00:14:05,110
It says,
"Vongole with garlic, garlic, garlic."

373
00:14:05,177 --> 00:14:06,011
DO NOT FORGET THE GARLIC

374
00:14:06,078 --> 00:14:08,514
-Do not forget.
-Never forget garlic when making vongole.

375
00:14:08,581 --> 00:14:11,350
-Isn't that top too small for you?
-Yes, really. What is that?

376
00:14:11,417 --> 00:14:13,619
That has to be an advert
for a frozen shoulder medicine.

377
00:14:14,787 --> 00:14:16,388
"When you can't lift your arm,

378
00:14:16,455 --> 00:14:18,524
-take this frozen shoulder medicine."
-I guess it is.

379
00:14:18,591 --> 00:14:21,994
-Frozen shoulder.
-And because he's a chef, the top

380
00:14:22,061 --> 00:14:23,729
-is a mustard color.
-Yes.

381
00:14:24,163 --> 00:14:24,997
LAUGHING OUT LOUD

382
00:14:25,064 --> 00:14:26,866
-Does it remind you of mustard?
-Or pea soup.

383
00:14:26,932 --> 00:14:29,501
Well, people do call it a mustard color.

384
00:14:29,568 --> 00:14:31,370
-The mustard color.
-People call it mustard.

385
00:14:31,437 --> 00:14:33,439
There's another one.
He had a photo shoot too?

386
00:14:34,773 --> 00:14:36,542
WHAT IS THAT?

387
00:14:36,609 --> 00:14:37,910
LAUGHING HARD

388
00:14:37,977 --> 00:14:39,411
That's gross. What is that?

389
00:14:39,478 --> 00:14:41,547
-He's a head on a platter.
-What's the theme?

390
00:14:41,614 --> 00:14:43,148
I have no idea.

391
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:44,216
Was that Photoshopped?

392
00:14:44,283 --> 00:14:45,751
-It wasn't.
-That's real?

393
00:14:45,818 --> 00:14:48,754
-It must've been a tough shot.
-Right?

394
00:14:48,821 --> 00:14:50,189
How did you do that?

395
00:14:50,890 --> 00:14:51,991
LIKE THIS

396
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:55,327
HE'S SITTING HERE…

397
00:14:55,394 --> 00:14:57,496
They wanted me to make a chic face.

398
00:14:57,563 --> 00:14:59,665
They couldn't have steamed
a dumpling that big,

399
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:01,066
yet that's a steamer lid.

400
00:15:01,133 --> 00:15:03,836
-You can't close the lid.
-That's the steamer lid.

401
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:06,405
Whose photos did you think
looked the best?

402
00:15:06,472 --> 00:15:07,339
Him.

403
00:15:07,406 --> 00:15:08,240
TOOK 0.1 SECONDS

404
00:15:08,307 --> 00:15:09,642
THANK YOU

405
00:15:09,708 --> 00:15:10,709
There's no need to ask.

406
00:15:10,776 --> 00:15:12,177
It's not that he was cool.

407
00:15:12,244 --> 00:15:14,680
It felt more comfortable to look at.

408
00:15:14,747 --> 00:15:16,582
He seemed awkward,

409
00:15:16,649 --> 00:15:19,618
-and he also seemed awkward.
-Did you feel awkward?

410
00:15:19,685 --> 00:15:20,853
Awkward.

411
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:22,821
THE PHOTOS WERE AWKWARD TO LOOK AT

412
00:15:22,888 --> 00:15:24,223
-All right, then.
-I'm jealous.

413
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:26,625
It's now time to turn

414
00:15:26,692 --> 00:15:31,196
the energetic Gen Z grandma,
Young-ok's fridge inside out.

415
00:15:31,263 --> 00:15:35,301
Because she is currently
the eldest active actor in Korea,

416
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:38,737
you may think she is old-fashioned.

417
00:15:38,804 --> 00:15:42,041
However, we believe that you are
well-versed in Gen Z culture.

418
00:15:42,107 --> 00:15:43,275
Goodness.

419
00:15:43,342 --> 00:15:46,345
-Gen Z kids often use their own slang.
-You're right.

420
00:15:46,412 --> 00:15:49,381
So, by any chance,
do you know any recent buzzwords?

421
00:15:49,448 --> 00:15:50,516
-Anything?
-You know.

422
00:15:50,582 --> 00:15:52,351
The deadass series.

423
00:15:52,418 --> 00:15:53,585
-Sorry?
-"The deadass series"?

424
00:15:53,652 --> 00:15:56,588
The deadass series. Deadass pissed.
Deadass mad. Deadass annoyed.

425
00:15:56,989 --> 00:15:59,658
NOW THAT'S THE DEADASS SERIES

426
00:15:59,725 --> 00:16:02,895
-Deadass hopeless. Things like that.
-Deadass hopeless.

427
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:04,964
-You know what "Deadass hopeless" is.
-Deadass hopeless.

428
00:16:05,030 --> 00:16:06,765
Also, WMITSTWB.

429
00:16:06,832 --> 00:16:08,767
What matters is the spirit
that won't break.

430
00:16:08,834 --> 00:16:11,670
-Or even going on broken.
-There are a few I know.

431
00:16:11,737 --> 00:16:13,172
You have an open mind.

432
00:16:13,238 --> 00:16:15,741
-Reality check. Something like that.
-Reality check.

433
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:18,711
-Reality check.
-When you tell us how the dishes are,

434
00:16:18,777 --> 00:16:21,413
can you mix in some of this Gen Z slang?

435
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,949
After you eat it, you can go,
"I'm deadass pissed."

436
00:16:24,016 --> 00:16:25,884
-"It's deadass fire."
-Yes.

437
00:16:25,951 --> 00:16:27,553
This is hopeless.

438
00:16:28,454 --> 00:16:29,288
Hopeless.

439
00:16:29,355 --> 00:16:31,323
We're about to open your fridge.

440
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:33,959
-Goodness.
-But you've been looking worried.

441
00:16:34,026 --> 00:16:36,562
It's a fridge that we old folks use,

442
00:16:36,628 --> 00:16:38,464
so it may seem shabby.

443
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:39,865
It's embarrassing.

444
00:16:39,932 --> 00:16:43,702
Ever since I got married,
I've spent the last 66 years homemaking,

445
00:16:43,769 --> 00:16:46,505
and it'll show in my fridge.

446
00:16:46,572 --> 00:16:48,741
So you know,

447
00:16:48,807 --> 00:16:51,677
-it's a bit embarrassing.
-I see. Don't say that.

448
00:16:51,744 --> 00:16:55,914
Who are you sharing this fridge with?

449
00:16:55,981 --> 00:17:00,786
I'm sure you all know that
I've been looking after my sick grandson.

450
00:17:00,853 --> 00:17:05,290
-So it's him and my husband.
-I see.

451
00:17:05,357 --> 00:17:09,028
What kind of ingredients
does she keep in her fridge?

452
00:17:09,094 --> 00:17:11,764
-We present Young-ok's fridge!
-Fridge!

453
00:17:12,331 --> 00:17:14,366
WOW

454
00:17:14,433 --> 00:17:15,401
-Fridge!
-Fridge!

455
00:17:15,467 --> 00:17:17,770
PRESENTING YOUNG-OK'S FRIDGE

456
00:17:17,836 --> 00:17:19,705
It's neatly organized! Not shabby at all.

457
00:17:19,772 --> 00:17:21,273
Everything looks great.

458
00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:22,674
It looks so neat.

459
00:17:22,741 --> 00:17:26,245
I usually don't stash
things in black plastic bags like that,

460
00:17:26,311 --> 00:17:27,913
but I was in a bit of a hurry.

461
00:17:27,980 --> 00:17:30,149
-Did you get it at the marketplace?
-I did.

462
00:17:30,215 --> 00:17:33,118
I always see these black plastic bags
from the marketplace at my mom's place.

463
00:17:33,185 --> 00:17:35,954
-Yes. Everyone does that.
-Everyone does that.

464
00:17:36,021 --> 00:17:37,256
The top shelf.

465
00:17:37,322 --> 00:17:40,125
These look pickled.

466
00:17:40,192 --> 00:17:42,094
Also, three apples.

467
00:17:42,161 --> 00:17:44,396
There are apples and…

468
00:17:44,463 --> 00:17:46,899
-Boiled eggs?
-I boiled some eggs.

469
00:17:46,965 --> 00:17:51,537
I boil eggs and eat half an apple
and one egg for breakfast.

470
00:17:51,603 --> 00:17:53,105
It's soft-boiled.

471
00:17:53,172 --> 00:17:54,807
-I see.
-Is this your breakfast?

472
00:17:54,873 --> 00:17:56,442
You'll see some gingko nuts too.

473
00:17:56,508 --> 00:17:59,011
-Do you have gingko nuts here?
-I'm almost done.

474
00:17:59,078 --> 00:18:02,014
So these. You eat a simple breakfast.

475
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:04,016
What do you usually eat
for lunch and dinner?

476
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:06,185
Rice and soup, the usual.

477
00:18:06,251 --> 00:18:08,754
<i>Bugeo-guk, miyeok-guk, kong-namul-guk,</i>

478
00:18:08,821 --> 00:18:12,091
<i>kimchi-guk, doenjang-jjigae,</i> and such.

479
00:18:12,157 --> 00:18:14,860
Do you have a special recipe
for soups and stews?

480
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:19,932
I have a habit of throwing in
a handful of meat into <i>doenjang-jjigae.</i>

481
00:18:19,998 --> 00:18:22,534
Also, when I make <i>kimchi-jjigae,</i>

482
00:18:22,601 --> 00:18:25,437
I don't like to use pork
just as most people do.

483
00:18:25,504 --> 00:18:28,407
So I always make anchovy broth
and make the stew with that.

484
00:18:28,474 --> 00:18:29,808
Anchovy broth.

485
00:18:29,875 --> 00:18:31,376
The stew is clearer.

486
00:18:31,443 --> 00:18:35,180
Also, I always add a bit of gochujang.

487
00:18:35,247 --> 00:18:36,181
That's my secret.

488
00:18:36,248 --> 00:18:37,816
-It's delicious.
-It sounds good.

489
00:18:37,883 --> 00:18:39,751
I also see many <i>jeotgal</i>, salted seafood.

490
00:18:39,818 --> 00:18:42,421
Clam, shrimp,

491
00:18:42,488 --> 00:18:45,357
-and what is this?
-Shrimp <i>jeotgal.</i>

492
00:18:45,424 --> 00:18:47,092
It says "New kimchi,

493
00:18:47,159 --> 00:18:49,561
made by us."

494
00:18:49,628 --> 00:18:51,096
"Made by us"?

495
00:18:51,163 --> 00:18:52,097
Did you make this?

496
00:18:52,164 --> 00:18:54,166
I made it as content
for my YouTube channel.

497
00:18:54,233 --> 00:18:56,101
-I made it myself.
-I see.

498
00:18:56,168 --> 00:18:58,137
Not only did we pick out
delicious napa cabbage,

499
00:18:58,203 --> 00:19:00,873
but everything else
turned out very delicious too.

500
00:19:00,939 --> 00:19:03,175
-I can smell it already.
-Try some.

501
00:19:03,242 --> 00:19:05,978
My family can't do without kimchi,
so I always need a lot in stock

502
00:19:06,044 --> 00:19:08,514
to make <i>kimchi-guk, kimchi-jjigae,</i>
stir-fried kimchi,

503
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:10,382
and we often eat kimchi fried rice.

504
00:19:10,449 --> 00:19:12,684
-We always have to have kimchi.
-Kimchi.

505
00:19:12,751 --> 00:19:15,320
-This looks like green onion kimchi.
-Green onion kimchi.

506
00:19:15,387 --> 00:19:18,724
Yes, Jun-myun sent that to me.

507
00:19:18,790 --> 00:19:21,193
-You sent it to her?
-I only have that much left.

508
00:19:21,260 --> 00:19:25,097
She only sends little batches,
so I always think, "This is too little."

509
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:27,599
But the more I dig into it,
the bigger the batch seems.

510
00:19:27,666 --> 00:19:30,836
I still have a lot left
after eating quite a lot. It's delicious.

511
00:19:30,903 --> 00:19:33,906
Next, this thing
you got at the marketplace.

512
00:19:33,972 --> 00:19:36,942
She threw this in the fridge,
still in the black plastic bag.

513
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:39,278
Let's find out what's inside.

514
00:19:39,344 --> 00:19:41,647
-This is… Whoa.
-What is that?

515
00:19:41,713 --> 00:19:43,115
-Yellowtail?
-What is it?

516
00:19:43,182 --> 00:19:45,083
-It's… No, Spanish mackerel.
-Spanish mackerel.

517
00:19:45,150 --> 00:19:49,254
I often salt the fish and grill it.

518
00:19:49,321 --> 00:19:51,390
-Spanish mackerel.
-Spanish mackerel? Not tuna?

519
00:19:51,456 --> 00:19:53,058
-Yes, a Spanish mackerel.
-A Spanish mackerel.

520
00:19:53,125 --> 00:19:54,893
-That's huge.
-It's pretty big.

521
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:58,130
-And cod.
-My family always eats

522
00:19:58,197 --> 00:20:02,201
hearty <i>daegu-tang, </i>codfish soup,
in the winter.

523
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:04,236
-You make it spicy.
-I can do that,

524
00:20:04,303 --> 00:20:08,207
and when my husband
doesn't want something spicy,

525
00:20:08,273 --> 00:20:09,908
-I make the clear soup too.
-The clear soup.

526
00:20:09,975 --> 00:20:11,877
You should join her round.

527
00:20:11,944 --> 00:20:13,378
Do you often eat Spanish mackerel

528
00:20:13,445 --> 00:20:14,746
-or cod in winter?
-I often use those.

529
00:20:14,813 --> 00:20:19,051
-Cod is best when the weather is colder.
-They're the best.

530
00:20:19,117 --> 00:20:21,520
I often tell people
to eat the food that is in season.

531
00:20:21,587 --> 00:20:24,356
-Brown croakers are for summer.
-August.

532
00:20:24,423 --> 00:20:28,160
Octopus for fall and clams for spring.
I remember these things.

533
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:30,529
-You remember the seasons accurately.
-Of course.

534
00:20:30,596 --> 00:20:33,098
That's the least I can memorize
after living this long.

535
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:35,901
It'd be nice if the chefs whip up
a nice bowl of <i>daegu-tang</i> today.

536
00:20:35,968 --> 00:20:38,036
-I agree.
-Right?

537
00:20:38,103 --> 00:20:40,639
-Clear <i>daegu-tang.</i>
-This cod looks delicious.

538
00:20:40,706 --> 00:20:44,476
Why don't you change your order
to a delicious bowl of <i>daegu-tang?</i>

539
00:20:44,543 --> 00:20:46,345
Let's give the star
to whoever makes that soup.

540
00:20:46,411 --> 00:20:48,513
If it's not good,
you'll be deadass hopeless.

541
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:49,848
She'll be deadass annoyed.

542
00:20:49,915 --> 00:20:52,484
A deadass hopeless
who can't even make <i>daegu-tang.</i>

543
00:20:52,551 --> 00:20:54,987
It'd be nice if one of the chefs made
an amazing bowl of soup.

544
00:20:55,053 --> 00:20:57,589
I see some vegetables down here.

545
00:20:57,656 --> 00:20:59,057
-Perilla leaves.
-Crown daisy.

546
00:20:59,124 --> 00:21:00,559
-Water parsley.
-Water parsley.

547
00:21:00,626 --> 00:21:04,029
You must always parboil
or boil water parsley in hot water.

548
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:06,098
-Water parsley.
-What's this?

549
00:21:06,164 --> 00:21:07,532
-Crown daisy.
-Is this a crown daisy?

550
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:10,102
-Yes, I often use it to cook.
-Crown daisy.

551
00:21:10,168 --> 00:21:12,104
-I add it on top…
-Because you eat lots of fish.

552
00:21:12,170 --> 00:21:16,141
-…whenever I make fish soups.
-It makes the soup refreshing.

553
00:21:16,208 --> 00:21:18,744
You need to top <i>daegu-tang</i>
with some crown daisy.

554
00:21:18,810 --> 00:21:21,680
Now, the freezer. The freezer is full too.

555
00:21:21,747 --> 00:21:23,849
-Shiitake.
-Yes.

556
00:21:23,915 --> 00:21:25,651
These look… One moment.

557
00:21:25,717 --> 00:21:27,552
EMBARRASSED

558
00:21:27,619 --> 00:21:29,321
-Look at these.
-Wait a second.

559
00:21:29,388 --> 00:21:30,956
Is that raw mussel meat?

560
00:21:31,023 --> 00:21:32,557
Oyster. She has oysters.

561
00:21:32,624 --> 00:21:33,825
You brought everything.

562
00:21:33,892 --> 00:21:35,427
-These are all prepped.
-Shrimps.

563
00:21:35,494 --> 00:21:36,795
It's not a big deal.

564
00:21:36,862 --> 00:21:38,897
-And are these Pacific saury?
-Pacific saury?

565
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:40,399
-She keeps them like this.
-Saury?

566
00:21:40,465 --> 00:21:43,035
These are very delicious in this season.

567
00:21:43,101 --> 00:21:45,370
-They're delicious now.
-It's rather inexpensive,

568
00:21:45,437 --> 00:21:49,041
so I salted them and froze them.
They're so good when grilled.

569
00:21:49,107 --> 00:21:51,076
-Cart bars do that.
-I see.

570
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:52,311
I see some meat.

571
00:21:52,377 --> 00:21:54,046
-Beef.
-She has all kinds of delicacies.

572
00:21:54,112 --> 00:21:56,481
These are rather frozen, though.

573
00:21:56,548 --> 00:21:59,685
When we need to eat in a hurry,
we'll make some steak

574
00:21:59,751 --> 00:22:01,987
-or grill them the Korean way too.
-Steak in a hurry.

575
00:22:02,054 --> 00:22:05,190
At times, I make bulgogi too,
but I don't think I brought the right cut.

576
00:22:05,257 --> 00:22:08,226
-Do you eat more seafood than red meat?
-Mostly.

577
00:22:08,293 --> 00:22:10,362
I have to remind myself to eat some meat.

578
00:22:10,429 --> 00:22:15,600
But I like it. When I make steak at home,
I do it properly.

579
00:22:16,535 --> 00:22:19,671
Next, let's take a look
at the room temperature ingredients.

580
00:22:19,738 --> 00:22:22,074
These sauces are all for Western cuisine.

581
00:22:22,140 --> 00:22:23,809
Do you use these often?

582
00:22:23,875 --> 00:22:26,545
-Balsamic vinegar?
-Not too often, but when my kids visit,

583
00:22:26,611 --> 00:22:30,615
my daughter or daughter-in-law
makes pasta for us,

584
00:22:30,682 --> 00:22:31,717
and they use those then.

585
00:22:31,783 --> 00:22:33,952
-And bread.
-I see lots of bread here.

586
00:22:34,019 --> 00:22:35,320
I love bread.

587
00:22:35,387 --> 00:22:36,588
What's your favorite?

588
00:22:36,655 --> 00:22:38,390
Don't people your age love
sweet red bean bread?

589
00:22:38,457 --> 00:22:39,758
Nothing with red beans.

590
00:22:39,825 --> 00:22:42,194
I prefer red bean porridge to bread.

591
00:22:42,260 --> 00:22:43,829
-You don't like the mix.
-She's set on it.

592
00:22:43,895 --> 00:22:46,698
I prefer salt bread
over sweet red bean bread.

593
00:22:46,765 --> 00:22:48,033
-Salt bread.
-Salt bread?

594
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:51,069
-She's seriously Gen Z. Salt bread?
-That's what I like.

595
00:22:51,136 --> 00:22:53,438
I like to eat a slice of baguette

596
00:22:53,505 --> 00:22:56,108
-with some cheese and butter on top.
-I guess you do.

597
00:22:56,174 --> 00:22:58,410
It seems like
you like your bread with cheese.

598
00:22:58,477 --> 00:22:59,444
Pizza bread.

599
00:22:59,511 --> 00:23:02,614
That was all for Young-ok's fridge!

600
00:23:02,681 --> 00:23:04,149
DONE CHECKING OUT YOUNG-OK'S FRIDGE

601
00:23:04,216 --> 00:23:09,020
Now, what orders
will she place for our chefs?

602
00:23:09,087 --> 00:23:12,057
Show us her orders!

603
00:23:13,425 --> 00:23:15,160
Both are revealed at the same time.

604
00:23:15,227 --> 00:23:16,561
The Old Woman and the Sea.

605
00:23:16,628 --> 00:23:18,897
-Queen's Dream.
-Like Hemingway.

606
00:23:18,964 --> 00:23:20,632
Combine them,
and you get the title of your play.

607
00:23:20,699 --> 00:23:22,300
You're right. <i>The Old Woman's Dream.</i>

608
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:24,069
-Yes.
-<i>The Old Woman's Dream.</i>

609
00:23:24,136 --> 00:23:25,570
These are references to your play.

610
00:23:25,637 --> 00:23:27,839
As for The Old Woman and the Sea,
what are you looking for?

611
00:23:27,906 --> 00:23:29,875
I don't mind what you make,

612
00:23:29,941 --> 00:23:31,743
but please use some fish

613
00:23:31,810 --> 00:23:34,112
that's good for the old folks.

614
00:23:34,179 --> 00:23:38,917
I want you to make a seafood dish
with the fish that's in season.

615
00:23:38,984 --> 00:23:41,186
Next, Queen's Dream.

616
00:23:41,253 --> 00:23:42,087
Yes, Queen's Dream.

617
00:23:42,154 --> 00:23:44,656
I'm sorry for my shabby fridge,

618
00:23:44,723 --> 00:23:47,626
but please use what I have
to make a delicious and stylish dish,

619
00:23:47,692 --> 00:23:49,528
something that the Queen would have.

620
00:23:49,594 --> 00:23:53,365
-It'd be nice if you did that.
-I see.

621
00:23:53,432 --> 00:23:54,966
-Please do that.
-An upscale dish.

622
00:23:55,033 --> 00:23:55,934
That's right.

623
00:23:56,001 --> 00:23:59,070
Now, who's going to take which order?

624
00:23:59,137 --> 00:24:01,773
She has lots of seafood,

625
00:24:01,840 --> 00:24:03,909
so I'll make
something delicious with them.

626
00:24:03,975 --> 00:24:06,511
He'll make something delicious
with her seafood.

627
00:24:06,578 --> 00:24:08,613
I'll join The Old Woman and the Sea too.

628
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:10,081
He's really fighting me.

629
00:24:10,148 --> 00:24:11,383
The brown croaker rematch?

630
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:13,652
Are you interested in the order
or Ho-young?

631
00:24:13,718 --> 00:24:15,020
Just Ho-young.

632
00:24:15,420 --> 00:24:16,555
CAME READY WITH HIS CANINE

633
00:24:16,621 --> 00:24:17,856
He's blind to the order.

634
00:24:17,923 --> 00:24:20,058
You do seem quite mad.

635
00:24:20,125 --> 00:24:22,427
-You've been waiting for this.
-You're angry.

636
00:24:22,494 --> 00:24:25,597
-It's his revenge for <i>Culinary Class Wars.</i>
-You're right.

637
00:24:25,664 --> 00:24:27,265
-Next, Queen's Dream.
-Queen's Dream.

638
00:24:27,833 --> 00:24:28,767
ME!

639
00:24:28,834 --> 00:24:31,336
-Hyun-suk raises his hand quietly.
-I knew it.

640
00:24:31,403 --> 00:24:32,537
SURPRISED

641
00:24:32,604 --> 00:24:34,873
-Chef Hyun-suk.
-What in the world?

642
00:24:34,940 --> 00:24:36,141
Need I say more?

643
00:24:36,208 --> 00:24:37,642
Yes, a bit more, please.

644
00:24:38,009 --> 00:24:40,178
INTERPRETATION: WHO ELSE WILL
MAKE THE QUEEN'S DREAM COME TRUE?

645
00:24:40,245 --> 00:24:43,415
If one of the chefs
must enter a palace and cook there,

646
00:24:43,482 --> 00:24:46,251
it should be you, Hyun-suk.

647
00:24:46,318 --> 00:24:49,354
Why were you so surprised
to see Hyun-suk take the order?

648
00:24:49,421 --> 00:24:51,990
It was surprising to know that
the future grandpa will cook.

649
00:24:52,057 --> 00:24:53,492
The future grandpa.

650
00:24:53,558 --> 00:24:55,227
-He's a fellow old folk.
-That's right.

651
00:24:55,293 --> 00:24:58,930
Who else will make her a queen
up against Chef Hyun-suk?

652
00:24:58,997 --> 00:25:01,533
-I'll join.
-Eun-yeong.

653
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:03,401
-The goddess.
-She's the queen of Chinese cuisine.

654
00:25:03,468 --> 00:25:05,937
-There are many stunning Chinese dishes,
-Yes.

655
00:25:06,004 --> 00:25:08,206
so I'll make something
and crown her as the Queen.

656
00:25:08,273 --> 00:25:10,308
-Goodness. Thank you.
-All right.

657
00:25:10,375 --> 00:25:13,512
-These are return matches, then.
-They are.

658
00:25:13,578 --> 00:25:16,615
The first round is a return match
after <i>Culinary Class Wars,</i>

659
00:25:16,681 --> 00:25:19,384
and the second is a return match
after our championship.

660
00:25:19,451 --> 00:25:21,152
Things are getting rough
so early in the year.

661
00:25:21,219 --> 00:25:24,523
Let us begin the round
between Ho-young and Sam!

662
00:25:25,557 --> 00:25:27,959
THE ROUND BEGINS NOW!

663
00:25:28,026 --> 00:25:32,264
<i>This is the first round played</i>
<i>with ingredients from Young-ok's fridge.</i>

664
00:25:32,330 --> 00:25:34,099
The man who said, "All I need is Sam,"

665
00:25:34,165 --> 00:25:35,500
Chef Ho-young is up.

666
00:25:35,567 --> 00:25:40,171
But Chef Sam joins this round and says,
"I'll do better without Ho-young."

667
00:25:40,238 --> 00:25:42,440
They've become the biggest enemies
after their time

668
00:25:42,507 --> 00:25:44,676
-in <i>Culinary Class Wars.</i>
-Goodness.

669
00:25:44,743 --> 00:25:48,013
It's a showdown here at <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

670
00:25:48,079 --> 00:25:49,881
This match was made possible

671
00:25:49,948 --> 00:25:53,218
because Sam wanted to teach Ho-young
a good lesson as we begin the new year.

672
00:25:53,285 --> 00:25:54,719
-He'll take him down.
-That's right.

673
00:25:54,786 --> 00:25:58,023
So? What's on your mind?
Do you think you lost because of him?

674
00:25:58,089 --> 00:25:59,190
Not exactly.

675
00:25:59,257 --> 00:26:01,159
But he ordered me around a lot.

676
00:26:01,226 --> 00:26:02,227
-Right.
-Yes.

677
00:26:02,294 --> 00:26:04,596
He said, "It'd be nice
if someone pushed down on the blender,"

678
00:26:04,663 --> 00:26:08,300
-and Sam was the only one around.
-I see.

679
00:26:08,366 --> 00:26:09,534
Did you expect him to do it?

680
00:26:09,601 --> 00:26:10,769
Was Sam that someone?

681
00:26:10,835 --> 00:26:12,604
-He was the only one there.
-Exactly!

682
00:26:12,671 --> 00:26:15,540
I honestly don't remember that moment.

683
00:26:15,607 --> 00:26:18,310
I was just talking to myself.
"It'd be nice if someone pushed it down."

684
00:26:18,376 --> 00:26:20,211
"I'm wasting time holding this down."

685
00:26:20,278 --> 00:26:21,379
-What about him?
-In the next shot,

686
00:26:21,446 --> 00:26:24,449
he was holding it down
as if I had put him up for it.

687
00:26:24,516 --> 00:26:27,018
Sam, why did you do that as he demanded?

688
00:26:27,085 --> 00:26:28,653
He's right. He was busy.

689
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:29,754
He was,

690
00:26:29,821 --> 00:26:31,990
but he was also a bit high-maintenance.

691
00:26:32,057 --> 00:26:33,024
As a team?

692
00:26:33,091 --> 00:26:34,759
-He wore him out.
-Exactly.

693
00:26:34,826 --> 00:26:36,428
-He made Sam exhausted.
-He wore him out.

694
00:26:36,494 --> 00:26:39,898
People might get fooled
by Ho-young's warm and kind looks,

695
00:26:39,965 --> 00:26:41,333
but he's a meticulous planner.

696
00:26:41,399 --> 00:26:43,101
-Me?
-"A meticulous planner"?

697
00:26:43,168 --> 00:26:45,470
Also, he's highly competitive.

698
00:26:45,537 --> 00:26:48,840
He kept taking jabs at Sam
to wear him down,

699
00:26:48,907 --> 00:26:50,175
then gave him one last big blow.

700
00:26:50,241 --> 00:26:51,810
THREW A COUNTERPUNCH AT THE DUEL

701
00:26:51,876 --> 00:26:53,979
-A sly fox.
-A chubby fox.

702
00:26:54,045 --> 00:26:55,947
Would you listen to yourselves?

703
00:26:56,014 --> 00:26:58,416
Why are you all judging them like this

704
00:26:58,483 --> 00:27:01,519
even before I try their dishes?

705
00:27:01,586 --> 00:27:03,021
That's not the case, ma'am.

706
00:27:03,088 --> 00:27:04,389
You're awful.

707
00:27:04,589 --> 00:27:06,458
A WORD OF WISDOM FROM THE ELDER

708
00:27:06,524 --> 00:27:07,959
She thinks we're serious.

709
00:27:08,026 --> 00:27:09,227
-It's friendly banter.
-We do that.

710
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:12,664
We joke around before we begin,
so it's more like professional wrestling.

711
00:27:12,964 --> 00:27:14,499
IN THAT CASE, OKAY…

712
00:27:14,566 --> 00:27:17,202
-It's to make them competitive.
-Then I'll have to judge them

713
00:27:17,268 --> 00:27:19,304
by their characters before I try the food.

714
00:27:19,804 --> 00:27:22,540
THE GEN Z GRANDMA ADAPTS QUICKLY

715
00:27:22,607 --> 00:27:25,276
Your theme in this round
is in-season seafood,

716
00:27:25,343 --> 00:27:27,879
and Ho-young has won every round
when he made seafood dishes.

717
00:27:27,946 --> 00:27:31,282
-It's tough to beat him with seafood.
-That's the case.

718
00:27:31,349 --> 00:27:33,718
He impressed many people
in <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>

719
00:27:33,785 --> 00:27:35,186
when he carved the monkfish.

720
00:27:36,388 --> 00:27:37,956
Even Chef Jong-won was surprised.

721
00:27:38,023 --> 00:27:41,226
The way he cut through the monkfish
reminded me

722
00:27:41,292 --> 00:27:42,861
of a tiger.

723
00:27:42,927 --> 00:27:45,330
-Tiger?
-A tiger who gnaws on a monkfish?

724
00:27:45,397 --> 00:27:47,232
So I named him the Monkfish Tiger.

725
00:27:47,298 --> 00:27:49,334
-Monkfish Tiger?
-I see.

726
00:27:49,401 --> 00:27:51,102
Can you go, "Rawr"?

727
00:27:51,169 --> 00:27:52,003
Rawr.

728
00:27:53,071 --> 00:27:54,406
-Rawr.
-Monkfish Tiger.

729
00:27:54,472 --> 00:27:57,676
What the heck are you all talking about?
I'm deadass annoyed.

730
00:27:58,143 --> 00:28:00,712
THE GRANNY TIGER ROARS

731
00:28:01,146 --> 00:28:03,481
WE'LL BEGIN THE BATTLE RIGHT AWAY

732
00:28:04,416 --> 00:28:06,351
CHEF SAM'S INGREDIENTS:
SPANISH MACKEREL, MUSSEL, OYSTER

733
00:28:06,418 --> 00:28:08,486
ZUCCHINI, WATER PARSLEY,
POTATO, CAPER, PEPERONCINO, PASTA

734
00:28:08,553 --> 00:28:11,589
Up first is Chef Sam. What are you making?

735
00:28:11,656 --> 00:28:13,291
I prepared a dish called

736
00:28:13,358 --> 00:28:15,360
Sam Will Push Jung Ho-young Down.

737
00:28:15,427 --> 00:28:18,229
-Push him down.
-Sam Will Push Jung Ho-young Down.

738
00:28:18,296 --> 00:28:20,532
Sam is saying he'll push Ho-young down.

739
00:28:20,598 --> 00:28:22,367
He's ready to push him down.

740
00:28:22,434 --> 00:28:25,670
Among the seafood you have,
Spanish mackerel is the best right now.

741
00:28:25,737 --> 00:28:29,007
I'll use that
with mussels, capers, and butter

742
00:28:29,074 --> 00:28:32,844
to make grilled Spanish mackerel
you probably have never had.

743
00:28:32,911 --> 00:28:34,546
-Grilled Spanish mackerel.
-Next,

744
00:28:34,612 --> 00:28:37,182
I'll use some water parsley
to add some aroma

745
00:28:37,248 --> 00:28:39,484
to a dish of oyster and mussel pasta.

746
00:28:39,551 --> 00:28:41,152
-Pasta?
-That sounds wonderful.

747
00:28:41,219 --> 00:28:44,289
-Will he have enough time? Two dishes?
-Will he have enough time?

748
00:28:45,123 --> 00:28:47,192
CHEF HO-YOUNG'S INGREDIENTS:
COD, COD MILT, KELP, WATER PARSLEY

749
00:28:47,258 --> 00:28:49,294
MINI CARROT, DRIED SHIITAKE, MISO SOUP,
YUJA PONZU SAUCE, BROTH TABLET

750
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:52,030
Ho-young has also taken this order.
What are you making?

751
00:28:52,097 --> 00:28:54,999
You had excellent cod in your fridge,

752
00:28:55,066 --> 00:28:58,369
-so I want to start a cod party.
-It's a party.

753
00:28:58,436 --> 00:29:00,572
I'll make a soup dish with cod meat.

754
00:29:00,638 --> 00:29:02,073
Like <i>daegu-tang?</i>

755
00:29:02,140 --> 00:29:05,243
It would seem similar,
but I wanted to make it richer.

756
00:29:05,310 --> 00:29:07,112
Then I saw some cod milt,

757
00:29:07,178 --> 00:29:08,346
so I'll use that

758
00:29:08,413 --> 00:29:12,317
and make a rich soup
that almost resembles fish porridge.

759
00:29:12,383 --> 00:29:13,585
-Will he blend the milt?
-Also,

760
00:29:13,651 --> 00:29:17,288
I'll deep-fry the cod milt as fritters
for you to have some on the side.

761
00:29:17,355 --> 00:29:18,356
-Fritters?
-Fritters.

762
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:19,891
That sounds so good.

763
00:29:19,958 --> 00:29:22,494
Which chef do you prefer
after hearing them talk about it?

764
00:29:22,560 --> 00:29:25,930
I'll have to see when they're done.
I don't want to say that carelessly.

765
00:29:25,997 --> 00:29:26,865
She doesn't want to share.

766
00:29:26,931 --> 00:29:28,767
-Okay, then.
-Just make it delicious.

767
00:29:28,833 --> 00:29:32,504
Monkfish Tiger and Canine Tiger
have both taken up Young-ok's order.

768
00:29:32,570 --> 00:29:36,574
Let us begin the round,
titled The Old Woman and the Sea.

769
00:29:36,641 --> 00:29:38,576
-Goodness gracious.
-Fifteen minutes.

770
00:29:38,643 --> 00:29:40,111
It's a rematch.

771
00:29:40,178 --> 00:29:42,647
Once again, this man is thinking,
"I hope someone loses for me."

772
00:29:42,714 --> 00:29:45,383
Monkfish Tiger, Chef Jung Ho-young is up.

773
00:29:45,817 --> 00:29:46,651
RAWR!

774
00:29:46,718 --> 00:29:49,420
Sam must be thinking,
"Ho-young, you're on your own!"

775
00:29:49,487 --> 00:29:53,258
Canine Tiger, Chef Sam Kim,
is also up for the challenge.

776
00:29:53,324 --> 00:29:56,661
The two white spoons are here
for their return match.

777
00:29:56,728 --> 00:29:58,463
Who will rise as the winner?

778
00:29:58,530 --> 00:30:01,933
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

779
00:30:03,668 --> 00:30:05,370
Begin!

780
00:30:05,436 --> 00:30:07,405
YESTERDAY'S FRIEND IS TODAY'S FOE!

781
00:30:07,472 --> 00:30:08,306
KELP

782
00:30:08,373 --> 00:30:11,409
-Kelp.
-He's using one piece here, many there.

783
00:30:11,476 --> 00:30:13,578
Is he boiling shiitake?

784
00:30:13,645 --> 00:30:16,247
-Dried shiitake.
-Dried shiitake?

785
00:30:16,314 --> 00:30:17,215
Cooking wine.

786
00:30:18,049 --> 00:30:19,250
For him, soup is everything.

787
00:30:19,317 --> 00:30:21,186
This is his chance to get revenge.

788
00:30:21,252 --> 00:30:25,290
Sam is also a chef
worthy of one of the top seven.

789
00:30:25,356 --> 00:30:29,627
Sadly, he was deceived
by Ho-young's scheming.

790
00:30:29,694 --> 00:30:30,728
His scheming?

791
00:30:32,030 --> 00:30:33,765
It resulted in Sam's elimination.

792
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:35,800
What's he using? A potato?

793
00:30:35,867 --> 00:30:36,901
POTATO & ZUCCHINI

794
00:30:36,968 --> 00:30:37,902
People only talked about

795
00:30:37,969 --> 00:30:39,470
-how he pushed down on the blender.
-Right?

796
00:30:39,537 --> 00:30:41,673
-He couldn't show off his skills.
-No.

797
00:30:41,739 --> 00:30:43,741
He only ran errands for Ho-young,
then his time was over.

798
00:30:43,808 --> 00:30:45,844
So today, Sam is here to get revenge.

799
00:30:45,910 --> 00:30:49,013
Will he be able to take Ho-young down?

800
00:30:49,080 --> 00:30:50,548
SAM IS HERE TO GET REVENGE!

801
00:30:50,949 --> 00:30:52,550
HOWEVER, IT'S HO-YOUNG AND SEAFOOD

802
00:30:52,617 --> 00:30:54,719
-Cod versus Spanish mackerel.
-That cod looks great.

803
00:30:54,786 --> 00:30:56,888
-It's so meaty.
-Wow.

804
00:30:56,955 --> 00:30:58,323
It looks great.

805
00:30:58,389 --> 00:30:59,924
He's preparing the cod.

806
00:30:59,991 --> 00:31:02,093
It looks nice and meaty.

807
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:04,529
QUICKLY CUTS OUT ANOTHER FILLET!

808
00:31:05,063 --> 00:31:05,964
THE REST BECOMES BROTH!

809
00:31:06,030 --> 00:31:07,432
He's using that to make broth?

810
00:31:07,498 --> 00:31:10,501
-Cod soup is nice and hearty in winter.
-It is.

811
00:31:10,568 --> 00:31:12,170
One concern I have is this.

812
00:31:12,237 --> 00:31:14,339
If the milt is delicious,
the meat is bound to be dry.

813
00:31:14,405 --> 00:31:15,540
That's true.

814
00:31:15,607 --> 00:31:17,542
I wonder how he'll cook that
to make it delicious.

815
00:31:17,609 --> 00:31:18,910
Make sure it's not dry.

816
00:31:18,977 --> 00:31:20,578
He's using starch…
Is that starch or flour?

817
00:31:20,645 --> 00:31:21,479
-Starch?
-Starch.

818
00:31:21,546 --> 00:31:23,715
If you coat it with starch
before cooking it,

819
00:31:23,781 --> 00:31:25,817
it coats the outside
so it's rich and velvety.

820
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:27,952
-That's right.
-So it adds a velvety texture?

821
00:31:28,019 --> 00:31:29,654
That's why he's the fish expert.

822
00:31:29,721 --> 00:31:31,522
-The Fish Guy.
-Yes.

823
00:31:31,589 --> 00:31:34,092
This is Spanish mackerel versus cod.

824
00:31:34,158 --> 00:31:35,526
The Spanish mackerel. Wow.

825
00:31:35,593 --> 00:31:36,828
SAM FIGHTS WITH SPANISH MACKEREL

826
00:31:37,629 --> 00:31:38,463
PREPPING THE PLUMP FISH!

827
00:31:38,529 --> 00:31:41,599
-Chef Sam is prepping the fish too.
-There's the Spanish mackerel.

828
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:44,602
Both fish are in season right now.

829
00:31:44,669 --> 00:31:47,805
You're right.
That Spanish mackerel is meaty.

830
00:31:47,872 --> 00:31:51,576
Chef Sam told her that
he'd make a new kind of grilled fish.

831
00:31:51,643 --> 00:31:53,411
He's stir-frying it with garlic.

832
00:31:54,345 --> 00:31:56,314
So he's not grilling it as is.

833
00:31:56,381 --> 00:32:00,952
-So it's not just an ordinary dish.
-It's good with capers.

834
00:32:01,019 --> 00:32:02,620
-He grabs some cod milt!
-Cod milt.

835
00:32:02,687 --> 00:32:04,722
-He said he'd deep-fry it.
-And blend it

836
00:32:04,789 --> 00:32:07,892
to probably turn it into a sauce.

837
00:32:08,593 --> 00:32:12,397
-That cod milt looks so good too.
-He's parboiling it.

838
00:32:12,463 --> 00:32:15,133
-He's parboiling the milt.
-That takes away the fishiness,

839
00:32:15,199 --> 00:32:16,701
and helps the frying batter stick.

840
00:32:16,768 --> 00:32:20,772
I see. No one is on par with Ho-young
when it comes to fish.

841
00:32:20,838 --> 00:32:22,173
He's a total expert.

842
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:24,809
He turned the milt
into tiny circular portions.

843
00:32:24,876 --> 00:32:26,411
PARBOILED MILT GOES INTO ICED WATER!

844
00:32:26,477 --> 00:32:28,146
It looks so good.

845
00:32:28,846 --> 00:32:30,281
THE REST GOES INTO THE BLENDER!

846
00:32:30,348 --> 00:32:32,483
He's using a blender.

847
00:32:32,550 --> 00:32:35,219
Sam usually helped him with those tasks.

848
00:32:35,286 --> 00:32:37,855
-It'd be nice if "someone" held on to it.
-Yes.

849
00:32:37,922 --> 00:32:39,924
But Ho-young could do it himself, anyway.

850
00:32:39,991 --> 00:32:43,328
Sam is at the point of neurosis
when he hears the blender whirr.

851
00:32:43,394 --> 00:32:44,395
FLINCHES

852
00:32:46,130 --> 00:32:47,031
BLENDED WITHOUT SOMEONE'S HELP

853
00:32:47,098 --> 00:32:49,867
-That happens when you grind melt.
-It looks like cream.

854
00:32:49,934 --> 00:32:51,736
-It's like fresh cream.
-It is.

855
00:32:51,803 --> 00:32:53,938
What's he doing now?

856
00:32:54,005 --> 00:32:56,207
-It's the frying batter.
-The frying batter.

857
00:32:56,274 --> 00:32:57,342
GLANCES

858
00:32:57,408 --> 00:32:58,910
Do you want someone to whisk that?

859
00:32:58,977 --> 00:33:00,478
He needs Sam's help.

860
00:33:00,545 --> 00:33:02,280
"SOMEONE" KEEPS POPPING IN HIS MIND

861
00:33:03,181 --> 00:33:04,615
Do you need help?

862
00:33:05,283 --> 00:33:06,551
CULINARY CLASS WARS MODE, ON

863
00:33:06,617 --> 00:33:08,019
No, I'm fine.

864
00:33:08,086 --> 00:33:09,988
ISN'T SURE IF HE SHOULD ASK FOR HELP…

865
00:33:10,054 --> 00:33:11,289
What's wrong?

866
00:33:11,356 --> 00:33:13,591
It's all right. I'm doing okay so far.

867
00:33:13,658 --> 00:33:15,093
Four minutes have passed.

868
00:33:15,159 --> 00:33:16,294
You have 11 minutes left.

869
00:33:16,361 --> 00:33:18,329
Goodness, time flew by.

870
00:33:18,396 --> 00:33:20,064
Yes, five minutes flew by in a flash.

871
00:33:20,131 --> 00:33:21,165
SUDDENLY WORRIED…

872
00:33:21,232 --> 00:33:23,134
WHAT ABOUT OUR CHEF SOMEONE?

873
00:33:23,201 --> 00:33:26,270
-He's grabbing mussels and oysters!
-Mussels and oysters.

874
00:33:28,406 --> 00:33:30,008
Peperoncino.

875
00:33:30,575 --> 00:33:31,642
WHAT'S THE NEXT STEP?

876
00:33:31,709 --> 00:33:33,911
He's dicing the mussels.

877
00:33:34,645 --> 00:33:36,147
Mussels and oyster meat.

878
00:33:37,181 --> 00:33:38,850
THE SPANISH MACKEREL SAUCE

879
00:33:38,916 --> 00:33:41,219
-That must be for the seafood pasta.
-It looks so good.

880
00:33:41,285 --> 00:33:42,787
Once it's done, it'll be fantastic.

881
00:33:42,854 --> 00:33:44,555
Sam's pasta is always good.

882
00:33:44,622 --> 00:33:45,923
That looks amazing too.

883
00:33:45,990 --> 00:33:47,358
Yes.

884
00:33:47,425 --> 00:33:48,393
It looks good.

885
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:50,228
NEXT, WATER PARSLEY!

886
00:33:50,795 --> 00:33:52,630
2. SEASON WATER PARSLEY AND BROIL

887
00:33:52,697 --> 00:33:53,664
Water parsley.

888
00:33:53,731 --> 00:33:56,467
What's on the gridiron?

889
00:33:56,534 --> 00:33:58,169
-Water parsley.
-Water parsley.

890
00:33:58,236 --> 00:33:59,537
-Are you broiling it?
-Yes.

891
00:33:59,604 --> 00:34:01,005
You're broiling water parsley?

892
00:34:01,072 --> 00:34:02,673
-That's so creative.
-Broiling water parsley?

893
00:34:02,740 --> 00:34:04,509
It looks good.

894
00:34:04,575 --> 00:34:06,511
It has a strong aroma,
so it's nice when smoked.

895
00:34:06,577 --> 00:34:08,246
CHOP UP AND FINISH PREPPING!

896
00:34:08,312 --> 00:34:11,149
Have you ever had broiled water parsley?

897
00:34:11,215 --> 00:34:13,151
No, I usually boil it.

898
00:34:13,217 --> 00:34:15,119
So you've only had it boiled.

899
00:34:15,186 --> 00:34:17,255
-He's using water parsley too.
-Water parsley.

900
00:34:17,321 --> 00:34:19,590
Ho-young is also using water parsley.

901
00:34:19,657 --> 00:34:21,926
I hear many international tourists
visit Korea these days

902
00:34:21,993 --> 00:34:24,262
because they're addicted to water parsley.

903
00:34:24,562 --> 00:34:26,531
IS THAT SO?

904
00:34:26,597 --> 00:34:28,633
-People come just to eat water parsley?
-Yes, many do.

905
00:34:29,233 --> 00:34:30,301
NO ONE BELIEVES HIM

906
00:34:30,368 --> 00:34:31,202
Seriously?

907
00:34:31,269 --> 00:34:33,504
-That was Kim Poong News.
-Sure.

908
00:34:33,571 --> 00:34:34,439
It's not factual.

909
00:34:35,173 --> 00:34:38,309
I didn't know people around the world
were into water parsley.

910
00:34:38,376 --> 00:34:39,777
It cleans your blood too.

911
00:34:39,844 --> 00:34:41,712
What are you chopping right now?

912
00:34:41,779 --> 00:34:43,981
-Mini carrots.
-Mini carrots.

913
00:34:44,048 --> 00:34:45,716
He's blanching the carrot.

914
00:34:46,451 --> 00:34:47,985
It's to bring out the colors.

915
00:34:48,553 --> 00:34:49,887
WHAT ABOUT THE SHIITAKE BROTH?

916
00:34:49,954 --> 00:34:50,888
SOY SAUCE

917
00:34:53,825 --> 00:34:54,725
WHAT'S HE POURING IN?

918
00:34:54,792 --> 00:34:56,861
What are you pouring in, Ho-young?

919
00:34:56,928 --> 00:34:57,895
What's that?

920
00:34:58,963 --> 00:34:59,797
What?

921
00:34:59,864 --> 00:35:01,332
It's miso.

922
00:35:01,399 --> 00:35:03,434
It's Japanese soybean paste.

923
00:35:03,501 --> 00:35:05,770
-It's not MSG, is it?
-It's not.

924
00:35:05,837 --> 00:35:07,338
-It looked like miso with MSG.
-No.

925
00:35:07,405 --> 00:35:09,640
Do people usually add
powdered miso to codfish soup?

926
00:35:09,707 --> 00:35:11,909
Young-ok doesn't seem to approve.

927
00:35:12,477 --> 00:35:14,679
THE MSG EXPERT INVESTIGATES

928
00:35:14,745 --> 00:35:16,080
It's MSG.

929
00:35:16,147 --> 00:35:17,915
It's miso with MSG!

930
00:35:17,982 --> 00:35:19,884
-Yes, it's seasoned.
-Right?

931
00:35:19,951 --> 00:35:21,486
Yes, it's very delicious.

932
00:35:21,552 --> 00:35:23,387
That's odd. Why is he using that?

933
00:35:23,454 --> 00:35:25,923
-Miso soup base doesn't sound right.
-This isn't right.

934
00:35:25,990 --> 00:35:29,360
Her trust in Chef Ho-young
slowly dwindles.

935
00:35:29,427 --> 00:35:31,095
You've spent over half of your time.

936
00:35:31,162 --> 00:35:33,197
-Oh, my.
-You have about seven minutes left.

937
00:35:33,264 --> 00:35:34,932
You're halfway done.

938
00:35:35,833 --> 00:35:37,468
You should
start grilling the Spanish mackerel.

939
00:35:37,535 --> 00:35:38,469
I'm about to.

940
00:35:38,536 --> 00:35:40,505
-Seven minutes and ten seconds.
-Seven minutes left.

941
00:35:40,571 --> 00:35:41,405
You should hurry.

942
00:35:41,973 --> 00:35:44,775
You planned for so many dishes.
How will you get them all done?

943
00:35:44,842 --> 00:35:46,944
It's his chance to get revenge.

944
00:35:47,011 --> 00:35:48,446
Does he have time to cook that?

945
00:35:51,516 --> 00:35:52,517
One moment.

946
00:35:52,583 --> 00:35:54,185
What's wrong? What is it?

947
00:35:55,953 --> 00:35:57,522
RUNNING AROUND IN CONFUSION

948
00:35:58,222 --> 00:35:59,724
Why are you at a loss?

949
00:35:59,790 --> 00:36:01,792
-I don't know.
-You don't know?

950
00:36:01,859 --> 00:36:03,227
-Then who can tell us?
-It's because

951
00:36:03,294 --> 00:36:05,363
-someone won't help!
-He's running around, confused.

952
00:36:05,429 --> 00:36:07,865
He can't do a thing without Sam!

953
00:36:07,932 --> 00:36:09,100
He just walks back and forth!

954
00:36:09,167 --> 00:36:12,770
-Sam must've helped with everything.
-Sam did all the actual work!

955
00:36:12,837 --> 00:36:13,905
You seem rather confused.

956
00:36:13,971 --> 00:36:15,506
He just needs to pause for ten seconds.

957
00:36:16,674 --> 00:36:18,409
Yes, you look confused.

958
00:36:18,476 --> 00:36:19,944
All of you tease each other.

959
00:36:20,011 --> 00:36:22,680
Do you need me to grab something?

960
00:36:22,747 --> 00:36:25,183
-What does he want to do?
-You've stopped again!

961
00:36:25,249 --> 00:36:26,484
-Dang it.
-What's wrong?

962
00:36:26,551 --> 00:36:28,452
-Nothing. I'm fine.
-What is it?

963
00:36:28,519 --> 00:36:29,587
The broth.

964
00:36:29,654 --> 00:36:31,756
Six minutes left. Six minutes!

965
00:36:31,822 --> 00:36:34,659
HE COMES TO HIMSELF
AND SCOOPS THE SHIITAKE BROTH

966
00:36:36,060 --> 00:36:39,130
-Ho-young scooped out some broth.
-You're mixing the two?

967
