1211
00:45:41,638 --> 00:45:44,041
When we grill this as is,
at times, it can feel a bit greasy.

1212
00:45:44,108 --> 00:45:46,643
<i>I usually use lemon juice</i>
<i>to keep the greasiness under control,</i>

1213
00:45:46,710 --> 00:45:48,846
<i>but he created this flavor</i>
<i>with something else.</i>

1214
00:45:48,912 --> 00:45:51,615
If he were doing this alone,
he would've been in first place.

1215
00:45:51,682 --> 00:45:52,983
WHOA!

1216
00:45:53,050 --> 00:45:55,753
-If you were doing this alone.
-He's in first place so far.

1217
00:45:55,819 --> 00:45:57,020
-The current first place.
-So far.

1218
00:45:57,087 --> 00:45:58,722
Ho-young's dish still waits.

1219
00:45:58,789 --> 00:46:00,591
Please try his dish too.

1220
00:46:01,291 --> 00:46:05,829
FRITTER AND CODFISH SOUP
MADE WITH COD MILT

1221
00:46:06,997 --> 00:46:11,335
RICH AND VELVETY SOUP
MADE WITH GROUND MILT

1222
00:46:12,569 --> 00:46:17,040
CHEF JUNG HO-YOUNG'S AMOR COD

1223
00:46:17,107 --> 00:46:18,809
He made the soup with ground milt.

1224
00:46:18,876 --> 00:46:20,878
This is cod milt, right? But I…

1225
00:46:20,944 --> 00:46:22,780
The cod milt is crucial.

1226
00:46:22,846 --> 00:46:26,283
Whenever I order <i>daegu-tang,</i>
I always ask for less milt

1227
00:46:26,350 --> 00:46:27,684
and eat just one or two pieces.

1228
00:46:27,751 --> 00:46:30,788
But I'll try this cod soup
and see what it's like.

1229
00:46:30,854 --> 00:46:32,923
That soup was also made with ground milt.

1230
00:46:32,990 --> 00:46:34,892
THE SOUP FIRST

1231
00:46:36,026 --> 00:46:37,427
The cod soup.

1232
00:46:37,494 --> 00:46:39,196
Is she frowning?

1233
00:46:40,097 --> 00:46:41,465
-She looks glad.
-She didn't.

1234
00:46:41,532 --> 00:46:42,966
WHAT DOES SHE MEAN BY THAT?

1235
00:46:43,033 --> 00:46:45,068
-What's going on?
-She's tough to read.

1236
00:46:45,135 --> 00:46:46,103
A LUMP OF MILT

1237
00:46:46,170 --> 00:46:47,204
And she tries the milt.

1238
00:46:50,674 --> 00:46:51,742
THAT HUM SAID IT ALL

1239
00:46:51,809 --> 00:46:53,811
She likes it. She thinks it's delicious.

1240
00:46:54,244 --> 00:46:55,779
STOOD TOO FAR AND COULDN'T HEAR HER

1241
00:46:55,846 --> 00:46:57,548
She likes it. She thinks it's delicious.

1242
00:46:58,649 --> 00:46:59,483
Is it okay?

1243
00:46:59,550 --> 00:47:01,819
Now this is how you cook cod milt.

1244
00:47:01,885 --> 00:47:05,823
It came from my fridge,
but I never knew how delicious this was.

1245
00:47:05,889 --> 00:47:07,558
-I see.
-Where is he?

1246
00:47:07,624 --> 00:47:10,727
-That guy made it. Ho-young.
-Yes, I see.

1247
00:47:10,794 --> 00:47:12,863
-And the cod.
-The chubby fox.

1248
00:47:12,930 --> 00:47:14,298
WHAT ABOUT THE CHUBBY FOX'S COD?

1249
00:47:14,364 --> 00:47:16,533
Ma'am, please dip the fillet in soy sauce.

1250
00:47:16,600 --> 00:47:19,236
-This?
-You can have it as is or with soy sauce.

1251
00:47:19,303 --> 00:47:21,939
<i>I see. But you made it</i>
<i>with water parsley, right?</i>

1252
00:47:22,005 --> 00:47:23,874
It's raw, though.

1253
00:47:23,941 --> 00:47:25,876
I'm a bit concerned because it's raw.

1254
00:47:25,943 --> 00:47:27,878
Then you don't need to dip it
in the sauce.

1255
00:47:29,413 --> 00:47:31,815
He added raw water parsley
into the soy sauce, right?

1256
00:47:31,882 --> 00:47:34,952
I'm a bit concerned
about how it's still raw,

1257
00:47:35,018 --> 00:47:37,054
but it won't kill me, so I'll try it.

1258
00:47:37,621 --> 00:47:39,690
-Will you try it?
-After all, he served it with the dishes.

1259
00:47:39,756 --> 00:47:40,757
The cod.

1260
00:47:41,458 --> 00:47:42,492
It must be good with the sauce.

1261
00:47:42,559 --> 00:47:44,895
AND?

1262
00:47:46,563 --> 00:47:47,965
Did I buy a good cod?

1263
00:47:48,031 --> 00:47:49,900
-Did she buy a good cod?
-Did I?

1264
00:47:49,967 --> 00:47:52,202
-Or did he cook it nicely?
-Or was it him?

1265
00:47:52,269 --> 00:47:53,704
It's so delicious.

1266
00:47:55,138 --> 00:47:57,007
BEAMING

1267
00:47:57,074 --> 00:47:59,376
And the milt soup.

1268
00:48:00,711 --> 00:48:01,945
She's enjoying it.

1269
00:48:02,012 --> 00:48:03,580
It seems like a restorative dish.

1270
00:48:03,647 --> 00:48:06,316
I said I didn't like cod milt,
but I'll eat it all today.

1271
00:48:06,383 --> 00:48:08,352
These go so well together.

1272
00:48:08,418 --> 00:48:09,319
I'm sorry,

1273
00:48:09,386 --> 00:48:12,189
but you didn't like the raw water parsley,
yet you keep eating it.

1274
00:48:12,256 --> 00:48:14,992
-I wanted a bite if she didn't finish it.
-There's the milt.

1275
00:48:16,293 --> 00:48:17,628
Didn't you broil it with a torch?

1276
00:48:17,694 --> 00:48:21,298
<i>Yes, I parboiled it</i>
<i>and then broiled it with a torch.</i>

1277
00:48:21,365 --> 00:48:23,533
-He's good with seafood.
-She keeps using the soy sauce.

1278
00:48:24,167 --> 00:48:26,003
-She keeps eating more.
-You can't beat that.

1279
00:48:26,069 --> 00:48:29,673
-She's on fire. She's getting started!
-She loves it.

1280
00:48:29,740 --> 00:48:32,042
-Chef Sam, what now?
-You said you didn't eat milt.

1281
00:48:32,109 --> 00:48:33,677
Sam, just hold on to that.

1282
00:48:33,744 --> 00:48:35,045
DESTINED TO HOLD SOMETHING FOR LIFE

1283
00:48:35,112 --> 00:48:37,447
-Dip the fritter in some salt.
-I'll try this too.

1284
00:48:37,514 --> 00:48:39,449
-Dip it in salt.
-This is…

1285
00:48:39,516 --> 00:48:41,852
It's hot on the inside,
so please be careful.

1286
00:48:41,919 --> 00:48:43,086
It's hot, so please be careful.

1287
00:48:43,153 --> 00:48:45,455
It's not hot anymore.
It's been sitting here for a while.

1288
00:48:45,522 --> 00:48:48,025
IT'S NOT HOT(?), SO I'LL EAT IT IN A BITE!

1289
00:48:50,193 --> 00:48:51,695
-It must be hot.
-It's hot.

1290
00:48:52,396 --> 00:48:54,331
-It's not hot.
-It's just good.

1291
00:48:54,398 --> 00:48:55,866
-It's cold.
-It's cold.

1292
00:48:56,433 --> 00:48:58,435
THE TOUGH GEN Z WOMAN

1293
00:48:58,502 --> 00:48:59,603
-It's cold?
-It must be hot.

1294
00:48:59,670 --> 00:49:02,940
Which do you like better between
the milt in the soup and the fritter?

1295
00:49:03,006 --> 00:49:05,842
-It doesn't matter. This is good too.
-They're both good?

1296
00:49:05,909 --> 00:49:08,578
-They're both good.
-She usually doesn't enjoy milt.

1297
00:49:08,645 --> 00:49:12,215
-You can't beat that.
-She's fascinated by how good it is.

1298
00:49:12,282 --> 00:49:14,651
-It looks good.
-I want to try some too.

1299
00:49:14,718 --> 00:49:17,154
But I can't help it.

1300
00:49:17,220 --> 00:49:19,189
It's not a matter of your talent.

1301
00:49:19,256 --> 00:49:21,291
-It's about my preference.
-That's right.

1302
00:49:21,358 --> 00:49:23,226
-You're right.
-That's it.

1303
00:49:23,293 --> 00:49:26,596
Let's try Chef Sam's dish,
Sam Will Push Jung Ho-young Down.

1304
00:49:26,663 --> 00:49:29,700
-The water parsley goes so well with this.
-How did he do this?

1305
00:49:29,766 --> 00:49:31,368
-It's so good.
-This pasta.

1306
00:49:31,435 --> 00:49:33,370
He always has that one kick.

1307
00:49:33,437 --> 00:49:34,638
ALREADY DONE

1308
00:49:34,705 --> 00:49:37,174
When something seems too much,
something else cuts in.

1309
00:49:37,941 --> 00:49:40,143
-It's seasoned excellently.
-Isn't it?

1310
00:49:40,210 --> 00:49:44,181
I often don't finish my pasta
when it's too bland,

1311
00:49:44,247 --> 00:49:45,849
but that one was just how I like it.

1312
00:49:45,916 --> 00:49:47,784
It's seasoned perfectly.

1313
00:49:47,851 --> 00:49:50,387
-It's good.
-It's not too bland.

1314
00:49:50,454 --> 00:49:55,025
I personally like pasta that brings out
the flavor of the ingredients,

1315
00:49:55,092 --> 00:49:56,860
and it's actually tough to find.

1316
00:49:56,927 --> 00:49:58,729
This was a type of pasta I love.

1317
00:49:58,795 --> 00:50:02,132
I love smoked oysters,

1318
00:50:02,199 --> 00:50:05,435
<i>so I like how the broiled water parsley</i>
<i>adds that smoky flavor</i>

1319
00:50:05,502 --> 00:50:07,471
to the oysters.

1320
00:50:08,672 --> 00:50:09,506
He always delivers.

1321
00:50:10,173 --> 00:50:11,708
That's Amor Cod.

1322
00:50:11,775 --> 00:50:13,010
It's milt soup, right?

1323
00:50:13,076 --> 00:50:16,013
-We didn't get any cod, but just milt.
-Let's try it.

1324
00:50:17,347 --> 00:50:18,582
I've never had soup like this.

1325
00:50:19,649 --> 00:50:21,351
-That soup is good.
-It's so new.

1326
00:50:21,418 --> 00:50:22,252
Wow.

1327
00:50:22,319 --> 00:50:24,187
NEXT, MILT FRITTER

1328
00:50:24,254 --> 00:50:25,088
This fritter.

1329
00:50:25,155 --> 00:50:26,723
SHOVES THE WHOLE THING IN

1330
00:50:26,790 --> 00:50:28,458
It reminds me of blowfish milt.

1331
00:50:28,525 --> 00:50:30,093
-It tastes so classy.
-How's the soup?

1332
00:50:30,160 --> 00:50:31,528
-It's wonderful.
-Is it?

1333
00:50:31,595 --> 00:50:35,198
Yes, it's very nice.
This flavor was unimaginable.

1334
00:50:35,265 --> 00:50:38,268
This soup reminds me
of beef tendon soup simmered for hours.

1335
00:50:38,335 --> 00:50:40,504
-I see.
-You know, the beef tendon soup.

1336
00:50:40,570 --> 00:50:44,608
The more you boil the soup,
the thicker it becomes.

1337
00:50:44,674 --> 00:50:46,076
I was reminded of that texture.

1338
00:50:46,143 --> 00:50:49,246
-I was amazed to feel that texture.
-You're right.

1339
00:50:49,312 --> 00:50:53,717
The way this milt fritter
melted away in my mouth

1340
00:50:53,784 --> 00:50:56,586
reminded me of something else
I recently had.

1341
00:50:56,653 --> 00:51:00,090
Didn't someone here make melon fritters?

1342
00:51:00,157 --> 00:51:01,925
Were you reminded of that?

1343
00:51:01,992 --> 00:51:04,594
-Me? Are you talking about me?
-He can't get over that thing.

1344
00:51:04,661 --> 00:51:07,464
-The melon felt like choux cream.
-Yes, I remember.

1345
00:51:07,531 --> 00:51:08,965
All thoughts lead to Poong.

1346
00:51:09,032 --> 00:51:10,934
It's time for you to decide.

1347
00:51:11,001 --> 00:51:13,770
-This is so hard.
-You heard comments from the fellow chefs.

1348
00:51:13,837 --> 00:51:15,806
<i>Press one to choose Sam</i>

1349
00:51:15,872 --> 00:51:17,841
<i>and two to pick Ho-young.</i>

1350
00:51:17,908 --> 00:51:20,911
-This is tormenting.
-The two with a history.

1351
00:51:20,977 --> 00:51:22,579
Please make your decision

1352
00:51:22,646 --> 00:51:24,781
and press the button.

1353
00:51:24,848 --> 00:51:26,316
-Did you press it?
-I did.

1354
00:51:26,383 --> 00:51:27,784
She did.

1355
00:51:27,851 --> 00:51:29,553
She pressed the button.

1356
00:51:29,619 --> 00:51:31,488
She has pressed the button.

1357
00:51:31,555 --> 00:51:33,990
Let's find out the result.

1358
00:51:34,057 --> 00:51:35,258
Show us!

1359
00:51:35,325 --> 00:51:37,828
The Old Woman and the Sea.
They both made in-season seafood dishes.

1360
00:51:37,894 --> 00:51:40,330
Oh, gosh. What now?

1361
00:51:40,397 --> 00:51:42,966
-I feel so bad.
-Will it be Monkfish Tiger, Ho-young?

1362
00:51:43,033 --> 00:51:44,868
Or will it be Canine Tiger, Sam?

1363
00:51:44,935 --> 00:51:47,504
Which dish did you like better?

1364
00:51:47,571 --> 00:51:49,072
The friends who became foes!

1365
00:51:49,139 --> 00:51:51,341
Who will take the star?

1366
00:51:51,408 --> 00:51:54,010
-Show us the result!
-I can't watch this.

1367
00:51:54,077 --> 00:51:56,813
Who won? Who's the winner?

1368
00:51:56,880 --> 00:51:58,949
SAM KIM WINS

1369
00:51:59,015 --> 00:52:00,750
CHEF SAM KIM'S
SAM WILL PUSH JUNG HO-YOUNG DOWN WINS

1370
00:52:00,817 --> 00:52:02,719
Sam Kim wins!

1371
00:52:02,786 --> 00:52:04,254
It's Sam's victory!

1372
00:52:05,355 --> 00:52:07,290
-He gets his revenge!
-That was so cool.

1373
00:52:07,357 --> 00:52:08,625
I feel so bad.

1374
00:52:08,692 --> 00:52:12,162
In the end, Young-ok chose Sam's dish.

1375
00:52:12,863 --> 00:52:14,431
But she enjoyed the soup so much.

1376
00:52:14,498 --> 00:52:18,201
-Yes, she enjoyed it very much.
-She kept sipping on the soup.

1377
00:52:18,268 --> 00:52:19,636
-It was good…
-It was.

1378
00:52:19,703 --> 00:52:21,805
…and it's great for the old folks.

1379
00:52:21,872 --> 00:52:25,842
<i>But he managed to make</i>
<i>the grilled fish not too greasy,</i>

1380
00:52:25,909 --> 00:52:30,413
and the pasta was something
I had never experienced before.

1381
00:52:30,480 --> 00:52:34,651
I wanted to give more points to someone
who made something that gave me…

1382
00:52:34,718 --> 00:52:36,486
-Yes, of course.
-…a new kind of experience.

1383
00:52:37,053 --> 00:52:39,256
-I'm sorry.
-Not at all.

1384
00:52:39,322 --> 00:52:41,158
That's why she's the Gen Z granny.

1385
00:52:41,224 --> 00:52:45,328
-She enjoyed both dishes happily…
-Well, that wasn't the reason.

1386
00:52:45,395 --> 00:52:47,931
…although they probably felt
new and unfamiliar.

1387
00:52:47,998 --> 00:52:49,733
This means

1388
00:52:49,799 --> 00:52:52,869
Sam, who had been hurt
since his defeat on <i>Culinary Class Wars,</i>

1389
00:52:52,936 --> 00:52:55,172
got his revenge against Ho-young…

1390
00:52:55,238 --> 00:52:57,107
-Gosh.
-…and won a star too.

1391
00:52:57,174 --> 00:52:58,441
Why don't we hear from him?

1392
00:52:58,642 --> 00:52:59,943
GLANCES

1393
00:53:00,010 --> 00:53:01,011
First of all,

1394
00:53:01,077 --> 00:53:04,581
I finally understand how he must've felt
when he defeated me and moved on.

1395
00:53:05,148 --> 00:53:06,183
THIS WAS HOW IT FELT!

1396
00:53:06,249 --> 00:53:07,817
-I feel bad…
-Yes?

1397
00:53:07,884 --> 00:53:11,087
I feel bad, yet I can't help but smile.

1398
00:53:12,255 --> 00:53:15,091
-That was a beautiful round.
-Put it right above his name tag.

1399
00:53:15,158 --> 00:53:16,126
-Is that so?
-You can put

1400
00:53:16,193 --> 00:53:18,562
-a star on Chef Sam's chest.
-Good work.

1401
00:53:18,628 --> 00:53:19,963
Goodness. I feel so bad.

1402
00:53:20,030 --> 00:53:23,033
It's a moving day for Sam.
Please put the star right here.

1403
00:53:23,099 --> 00:53:24,134
Okay.

1404
00:53:24,201 --> 00:53:26,503
-Sam Kim!
-Congratulations!

1405
00:53:26,570 --> 00:53:28,405
-It's his first star of the year!
-Congrats!

1406
00:53:28,471 --> 00:53:30,173
Sam takes his first win

1407
00:53:30,240 --> 00:53:32,042
and gets his revenge on Ho-young.

1408
00:53:32,676 --> 00:53:36,713
<i>Next up is the second cook-off</i>
<i>with ingredients from Young-ok's fridge.</i>

1409
00:53:36,780 --> 00:53:40,250
The one who took the throne
in the 2025 season…

1410
00:53:40,317 --> 00:53:42,852
-You're right.
-…the Showoff King, Choi Hyun-suk.

1411
00:53:42,919 --> 00:53:44,721
He's up against someone who's on fire,

1412
00:53:44,788 --> 00:53:48,458
-the Strikeout Queen, Park Eun-yeong.
<i>-Strikeout!</i>

1413
00:53:48,525 --> 00:53:53,029
<i>These two fought in the final round</i>
<i>of last year's championship,</i>

1414
00:53:53,096 --> 00:53:55,765
and their return match
came much sooner than we thought.

1415
00:53:55,832 --> 00:53:59,236
Back then, I had to make
four different dishes on the same day,

1416
00:53:59,302 --> 00:54:01,972
so I was out of energy and ideas.

1417
00:54:02,038 --> 00:54:04,741
-But today, I only have to make one dish.
-Yes.

1418
00:54:04,808 --> 00:54:07,110
I believe I have a good chance.

1419
00:54:07,177 --> 00:54:08,478
That's Eun-yeong.

1420
00:54:08,545 --> 00:54:10,413
-If she played a single round back then…
-Yes.

1421
00:54:10,480 --> 00:54:12,649
-…she might have had a better chance.
-No one knows.

1422
00:54:12,716 --> 00:54:14,784
What she's trying to say is this.

1423
00:54:14,851 --> 00:54:16,720
Hyun-suk sat around all day long,

1424
00:54:16,786 --> 00:54:19,556
played one round, and became a champion.

1425
00:54:19,623 --> 00:54:21,458
He was so happy
with the trophy over his head.

1426
00:54:21,524 --> 00:54:23,593
<i>-He celebrated all alone.</i>
<i>-He did.</i>

1427
00:54:23,660 --> 00:54:25,528
-We had a team dinner that day, remember?
-Yes.

1428
00:54:25,595 --> 00:54:27,697
He crashed our table
and even grilled some meat.

1429
00:54:27,764 --> 00:54:30,333
-He still had energy left in him.
-He was fine.

1430
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:31,568
He would've had energy.

1431
00:54:31,635 --> 00:54:34,471
-He was so energetic.
-But Eun-yeong was like this in the back.

1432
00:54:34,537 --> 00:54:35,939
-She was exhausted.
-She was like this.

1433
00:54:36,406 --> 00:54:37,874
GIGGLING

1434
00:54:37,941 --> 00:54:40,744
She says the result would've changed
if you two played one round.

1435
00:54:40,810 --> 00:54:43,079
Don't you remember
what I made on that day?

1436
00:54:43,146 --> 00:54:44,981
Have ya… Have you all forgotten?

1437
00:54:45,048 --> 00:54:46,616
-What was it?
-I don't remember.

1438
00:54:46,683 --> 00:54:47,717
I don't even remember.

1439
00:54:47,784 --> 00:54:49,819
-What was it?
-It was last year, anyway.

1440
00:54:49,886 --> 00:54:51,755
-I made a Wellington.
-A Wellington.

1441
00:54:51,821 --> 00:54:54,190
-Yes, right.
-It was a seafood Wellington

1442
00:54:54,257 --> 00:54:56,860
that was near impossible to make
in 15 minutes.

1443
00:54:56,926 --> 00:54:59,195
No matter how high her energy was
and what she made,

1444
00:54:59,262 --> 00:55:01,131
that dish is unbeatable.

1445
00:55:01,831 --> 00:55:03,933
-It was the ultimate dish.
-I guess so.

1446
00:55:04,000 --> 00:55:06,670
But let's take a look at the data.

1447
00:55:06,736 --> 00:55:10,240
Chef Eun-yeong has never won
against Chef Hyun-suk.

1448
00:55:10,307 --> 00:55:13,443
The data shows that
she has never won, not even once.

1449
00:55:13,510 --> 00:55:15,378
<i>I think the moth to a flame</i>
<i>should do better.</i>

1450
00:55:15,445 --> 00:55:16,346
What? Really?

1451
00:55:16,413 --> 00:55:19,015
Actually, I did an analysis on him.

1452
00:55:19,082 --> 00:55:21,985
-Yes?
-All his dishes have a kick.

1453
00:55:22,052 --> 00:55:23,119
That's right.

1454
00:55:23,186 --> 00:55:24,988
He always has that kick
that hits you hard.

1455
00:55:25,055 --> 00:55:29,359
So I thought I should also add a kick
to hit her hard today.

1456
00:55:29,426 --> 00:55:31,995
So Hyun-suk is just a guy
who knows how to add a good kick?

1457
00:55:32,062 --> 00:55:33,830
That single kick is the only thing

1458
00:55:33,897 --> 00:55:35,832
that allows him to make a living.

1459
00:55:35,899 --> 00:55:38,168
-That's all he uses to earn stars.
-And get stars.

1460
00:55:38,234 --> 00:55:39,269
What a shame.

1461
00:55:39,336 --> 00:55:41,638
Did you really think I only had one kick?

1462
00:55:41,905 --> 00:55:43,139
CHUCKLING

1463
00:55:43,206 --> 00:55:44,341
Do you have many kicks?

1464
00:55:44,741 --> 00:55:46,343
ANSWERS WITH A SMILE

1465
00:55:46,409 --> 00:55:48,745
All right. The order she put in
is titled Queen's Dream.

1466
00:55:48,812 --> 00:55:52,482
Another important aspect is
which country she will be the Queen of.

1467
00:55:52,549 --> 00:55:55,218
In the photo shoot she shared with us,

1468
00:55:55,285 --> 00:55:57,987
she made an homage
to the Queen of England.

1469
00:55:58,054 --> 00:55:59,322
So through my dish,

1470
00:55:59,389 --> 00:56:00,924
I'll make her the Queen of France.

1471
00:56:00,990 --> 00:56:03,259
-The Queen of France.
-He's making a French dish.

1472
00:56:03,326 --> 00:56:05,595
He'll make you the Queen of France.

1473
00:56:05,662 --> 00:56:07,097
-I guess he's making French.
-Yes.

1474
00:56:07,163 --> 00:56:08,531
What about you, Chef Eun-yeong?

1475
00:56:08,598 --> 00:56:11,301
This year, my grandmother

1476
00:56:11,368 --> 00:56:12,769
is 97 years old,

1477
00:56:12,836 --> 00:56:14,871
-but she's still going strong.
-Really?

1478
00:56:14,938 --> 00:56:17,941
I'd cook for her from time to time
before I became this busy,

1479
00:56:18,007 --> 00:56:21,344
and she always loved it
and said Chinese cuisine was delicious.

1480
00:56:21,411 --> 00:56:23,613
So I'll think of this as a chance
to serve her as a queen

1481
00:56:23,680 --> 00:56:28,017
and make you the Queen
of the Chinese Royal Family.

1482
00:56:28,084 --> 00:56:29,452
-The Imperial Family.
-Queen Dowager Ok.

1483
00:56:29,519 --> 00:56:30,620
They're very glamorous.

1484
00:56:30,687 --> 00:56:32,122
THE CHINESE QUEEN'S DREAM

1485
00:56:32,722 --> 00:56:33,923
I see.

1486
00:56:33,990 --> 00:56:36,025
-She even brought up her own grandmother.
-She did.

1487
00:56:36,092 --> 00:56:38,128
She threw in her personal story.

1488
00:56:38,194 --> 00:56:42,198
-That story may make Young-ok feel weak.
-That's possible.

1489
00:56:43,066 --> 00:56:45,268
CHEF HYUN-SUK'S INGREDIENTS:
SHRIMP, PORK BELLY

1490
00:56:45,335 --> 00:56:47,203
BACON, PERILLA LEAF, APPLE, CAPER, MILK

1491
00:56:47,270 --> 00:56:49,939
The name of the dish I'll make for you is

1492
00:56:50,006 --> 00:56:52,809
All Bow to the Grand Queen Shrimp!

1493
00:56:53,576 --> 00:56:54,477
POLITE

1494
00:56:54,544 --> 00:56:56,346
I see. You're using shrimps.

1495
00:56:56,413 --> 00:56:57,881
-Shrimps.
-Shrimps.

1496
00:56:57,947 --> 00:57:00,350
All Bow to the Grand Queen Shrimp!

1497
00:57:00,417 --> 00:57:01,885
What will you make?

1498
00:57:01,951 --> 00:57:04,120
As her cooking bodyguard,

1499
00:57:04,187 --> 00:57:06,890
I'll make everything
from start to finish with shrimp.

1500
00:57:06,956 --> 00:57:10,727
I'll be using this versatile ingredient
in a variety of ways

1501
00:57:10,794 --> 00:57:13,797
-and make shrimp terrine and cream
-Terrine?

1502
00:57:13,863 --> 00:57:16,366
to present a perfect dish for you.

1503
00:57:16,433 --> 00:57:19,335
So the Queen should
just eat shrimp and go home?

1504
00:57:19,402 --> 00:57:21,504
Do you think I'll serve ordinary shrimps?

1505
00:57:21,571 --> 00:57:23,840
I, Choi Hyun-suk…

1506
00:57:24,174 --> 00:57:25,308
CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY

1507
00:57:25,375 --> 00:57:26,810
I, Choi Hyun-suk, your bodyguard,

1508
00:57:26,876 --> 00:57:30,313
-will show you a new kind of shrimp dish.
-I see.

1509
00:57:31,247 --> 00:57:33,082
CHEF EUN-YEONG'S INGREDIENTS:
SHRIMP, PORK BELLY

1510
00:57:33,149 --> 00:57:35,318
DRIED SHIITAKE, WATER PARSLEY,
PEPERONCINO, OYSTER SAUCE

1511
00:57:35,385 --> 00:57:38,254
And chef Park Eun-yeong.
What will you be making?

1512
00:57:38,321 --> 00:57:40,356
The name of my dish is as follows.

1513
00:57:40,423 --> 00:57:42,325
The name of my dish is as follows.

1514
00:57:42,392 --> 00:57:43,927
-Meatball Queen?
-Yes.

1515
00:57:43,993 --> 00:57:46,529
-It's called Meatball Queen.
-She's making meatballs.

1516
00:57:46,596 --> 00:57:47,864
And you danced to "Queencard."

1517
00:57:47,931 --> 00:57:49,098
Your Royal Highness!

1518
00:57:49,165 --> 00:57:51,067
The female Ho-young is in your presence.

1519
00:57:51,901 --> 00:57:53,470
AN EMERGENCY FOR THE MALE HO-YOUNG

1520
00:57:53,536 --> 00:57:55,071
The female Ho-young is with us.

1521
00:57:55,138 --> 00:57:56,573
So are you making meatballs?

1522
00:57:56,639 --> 00:57:58,408
I prepared a meatball dish today.

1523
00:57:58,475 --> 00:58:00,777
There's a Chinese dish called lion's head.

1524
00:58:00,844 --> 00:58:01,978
Lion's head.

1525
00:58:02,045 --> 00:58:03,279
It's a meatball dish

1526
00:58:03,346 --> 00:58:05,448
-made to resemble a lion's head,
-Lion's head.

1527
00:58:05,515 --> 00:58:08,651
including some vegetables on the dish
to recreate its mane.

1528
00:58:09,152 --> 00:58:10,086
SMILING

1529
00:58:10,153 --> 00:58:12,889
Aren't lions considered
the king of animals?

1530
00:58:12,956 --> 00:58:15,091
That was why I prepared this

1531
00:58:15,158 --> 00:58:19,062
to serve Young-ok as my king,
no, my queen.

1532
00:58:19,128 --> 00:58:22,065
Who's going to be the winner?

1533
00:58:22,131 --> 00:58:26,069
Let us begin the next round,
Queen's Dream.

1534
00:58:26,135 --> 00:58:30,340
Today, he's here as the bodyguard
to the Grand Queen Dowager.

1535
00:58:30,406 --> 00:58:33,309
Chef Choi Hyun-suk,
the showoff king of the show.

1536
00:58:33,376 --> 00:58:35,178
The showoff king's age has fallen,

1537
00:58:35,245 --> 00:58:37,347
and her era has begun!

1538
00:58:37,413 --> 00:58:39,849
The rebellious queen of the show,

1539
00:58:39,916 --> 00:58:42,051
Chef Park Eun-yeong.

1540
00:58:42,118 --> 00:58:45,688
Which chef will receive a star
from the Queen?

1541
00:58:45,755 --> 00:58:48,324
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1542
00:58:49,192 --> 00:58:50,460
Fifteen minutes begin now.

1543
00:58:51,327 --> 00:58:53,830
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1544
00:58:54,430 --> 00:58:56,132
Make a dish to turn her into a queen.

1545
00:58:56,199 --> 00:58:57,534
They're both using shrimp.

1546
00:58:57,600 --> 00:59:00,870
-You're right. Eun-yeong uses a lot too.
-They're both using shrimp.

1547
00:59:00,937 --> 00:59:02,805
-They both use shrimp.
-Shrimp versus shrimp.

1548
00:59:02,872 --> 00:59:04,541
They're doing the same thing.

1549
00:59:04,607 --> 00:59:07,443
-Wait, Chef Hyun-suk grabs some meat.
-Is that pork belly?

1550
00:59:07,510 --> 00:59:09,779
-I added bacon to shrimp.
-Bacon.

1551
00:59:09,846 --> 00:59:11,080
-And?
-Pork belly.

1552
00:59:11,147 --> 00:59:13,550
-Pork belly. Wait, just the fat?
-The fat.

1553
00:59:13,616 --> 00:59:14,617
It's pork fat.

1554
00:59:14,684 --> 00:59:15,885
-I get it.
-Pork fat?

1555
00:59:15,952 --> 00:59:17,854
Wait, I've done this before.

1556
00:59:17,921 --> 00:59:19,556
-A dim sum technique.
-It's an homage to you.

1557
00:59:19,622 --> 00:59:21,424
Yes, are you paying homage to me?

1558
00:59:21,991 --> 00:59:25,094
-Totally understandable.
-Understandable.

1559
00:59:25,161 --> 00:59:26,296
The second-most buzzworthy man.

1560
00:59:26,362 --> 00:59:28,231
-Understandable.
-Yes.

1561
00:59:29,599 --> 00:59:31,367
He just seasoned the plastic wrap.

1562
00:59:31,434 --> 00:59:33,102
Did the salt make it in?

1563
00:59:33,169 --> 00:59:36,205
I don't think so.
He does this and then puts it in.

1564
00:59:36,272 --> 00:59:37,373
IN REALITY, HE'S COMPOSED

1565
00:59:37,607 --> 00:59:39,242
She's using pork belly too.

1566
00:59:39,309 --> 00:59:41,377
-She also uses meat.
-They use the same ingredients.

1567
00:59:41,444 --> 00:59:43,746
-Yes, they're similar.
-They're the same.

1568
00:59:43,813 --> 00:59:45,448
-It's the same.
-She uses it whole.

1569
00:59:45,515 --> 00:59:47,650
Their recipes seem almost identical.

1570
00:59:47,717 --> 00:59:48,551
They're the same.

1571
00:59:48,618 --> 00:59:51,287
He added some milk though.

1572
00:59:51,354 --> 00:59:53,556
It grinds more easily with some milk.

1573
00:59:53,623 --> 00:59:54,958
-That's different.
-She uses an egg.

1574
00:59:55,024 --> 00:59:56,459
She throws in an egg.

1575
00:59:56,526 --> 00:59:57,860
-Just the whites.
-Only the whites.

1576
00:59:57,927 --> 00:59:59,228
She's using egg whites.

1577
00:59:59,295 --> 01:00:00,396
Just the whites.

1578
01:00:00,463 --> 01:00:02,665
One uses milk, the other uses egg whites.

1579
01:00:02,732 --> 01:00:05,602
It's the difference
between Chinese and Western cuisine.

1580
01:00:05,668 --> 01:00:06,736
The difference between the two.

1581
01:00:08,438 --> 01:00:10,173
It's not working.

1582
01:00:10,239 --> 01:00:11,908
There's too much in it. That's all.

1583
01:00:12,508 --> 01:00:14,577
It'd be nice if someone could hold it.

1584
01:00:15,178 --> 01:00:17,013
It'd be nice
if someone could push it down.

1585
01:00:17,480 --> 01:00:18,581
STOP RIDING THE WAVE BEFORE WE BREAK

1586
01:00:18,648 --> 01:00:19,782
Gosh, seriously.

1587
01:00:19,849 --> 01:00:21,851
There's just too much in there.

1588
01:00:21,918 --> 01:00:24,020
-It begins to spin!
-It's working.

1589
01:00:24,087 --> 01:00:25,388
It's now grinding smoothly.

1590
01:00:27,190 --> 01:00:29,325
WELL, WE'RE RIDING THE WAVES ANYWAY

1591
01:00:29,392 --> 01:00:31,227
Chef Hyun-suk is done grinding everything.

1592
01:00:31,294 --> 01:00:32,562
Someone needs to hold it.

1593
01:00:32,629 --> 01:00:33,496
SO WE DECIDED TO GO ON

1594
01:00:33,563 --> 01:00:35,498
She can't hold that forever.

1595
01:00:35,565 --> 01:00:37,734
You don't have to grind it that long.

1596
01:00:37,800 --> 01:00:40,803
The meatball for the lion's head
needs to be quite big.

1597
01:00:40,870 --> 01:00:43,039
-She must need a lot, then.
-She does.

1598
01:00:43,106 --> 01:00:45,775
-Chef Hyun-suk grabs more shrimp.
-Shrimp.

1599
01:00:45,842 --> 01:00:47,744
He's surrounded by shrimp.

1600
01:00:47,810 --> 01:00:49,345
COVERED WITH A PLASTIC SHEET

1601
01:00:49,412 --> 01:00:51,948
He's pounding them flat.

1602
01:00:52,015 --> 01:00:53,616
He's pounding the shrimps.

1603
01:00:53,683 --> 01:00:55,251
Maybe that's why he added the word bow.

1604
01:00:55,318 --> 01:00:58,221
-He's making the shrimp bow down.
-Bowing flat.

1605
01:00:58,287 --> 01:01:00,390
That was something Poong often did.

1606
01:01:00,456 --> 01:01:02,358
I think Chef Hyun-suk is spectacular.

1607
01:01:02,425 --> 01:01:03,559
He's even willing to follow

1608
01:01:03,626 --> 01:01:05,795
-the recipe of a random webtoon artist.
-Look at him.

1609
01:01:05,862 --> 01:01:06,829
Paying an homage?

1610
01:01:06,896 --> 01:01:08,364
No chef would be willing to do that!

1611
01:01:08,431 --> 01:01:10,466
-All he wants is buzz.
-That's it.

1612
01:01:10,533 --> 01:01:11,668
Where does the salt go?

1613
01:01:11,734 --> 01:01:12,568
GROUND PEPPER

1614
01:01:13,836 --> 01:01:15,672
NEXT, THE GROUND SHRIMP MOUSSE

1615
01:01:16,172 --> 01:01:17,940
INTO A PIPING BAG

1616
01:01:18,908 --> 01:01:19,742
CUT!

1617
01:01:19,809 --> 01:01:21,744
-And?
-What now?

1618
01:01:21,811 --> 01:01:23,246
THE AGING CURVE

1619
01:01:23,513 --> 01:01:26,215
THE MOUSSE WAS A LITTLE IMPATIENT

1620
01:01:26,416 --> 01:01:27,884
BLURRY VISION

1621
01:01:27,950 --> 01:01:30,420
Will he put that inside?
I get it. That's not the terrine.

1622
01:01:30,486 --> 01:01:32,355
He's going to wrap it.

1623
01:01:32,422 --> 01:01:34,457
He put the mousse on top of the shrimp.

1624
01:01:34,524 --> 01:01:35,725
He's wrapping it.

1625
01:01:35,792 --> 01:01:37,627
-It's so hectic.
-Yes.

1626
01:01:37,694 --> 01:01:39,228
She feels that this is hectic.

1627
01:01:39,295 --> 01:01:41,230
Why are you so chaotic?

1628
01:01:41,297 --> 01:01:43,766
You should sit quietly when you cook!

1629
01:01:44,434 --> 01:01:46,703
EUN-YEONG IS DONE WITH THE BLENDER TOO

1630
01:01:46,769 --> 01:01:49,338
Chef Eun-yeong seems to be
seasoning the mix.

1631
01:01:49,405 --> 01:01:50,239
I am.

1632
01:01:51,007 --> 01:01:52,108
PATIENTLY, UNTIL PASTY!

1633
01:01:52,175 --> 01:01:53,109
She's so fast.

1634
01:01:53,176 --> 01:01:54,343
She only uses her hands.

1635
01:01:54,410 --> 01:01:56,012
That must be the meatball seasoning.

1636
01:01:56,079 --> 01:01:58,181
-What are those? Capers?
-Capers. She said she liked those.

1637
01:01:58,247 --> 01:02:01,150
-He picked it up right away.
-And uses it.

1638
01:02:01,217 --> 01:02:02,819
<i>I often use crown daisy to cook.</i>

1639
01:02:02,885 --> 01:02:05,488
<i>I add it on top</i>
<i>whenever I make fish soups.</i>

1640
01:02:05,555 --> 01:02:07,056
I REMEMBER THAT!

1641
01:02:07,123 --> 01:02:08,658
He remembered that she liked…

1642
01:02:08,725 --> 01:02:10,293
-Where are you going?
-What is it?

1643
01:02:10,359 --> 01:02:12,261
-What's wrong?
-Crown daisy.

1644
01:02:12,328 --> 01:02:13,896
What did you forget? Crown daisy?

1645
01:02:13,963 --> 01:02:15,665
It's down there. Yes.

1646
01:02:15,732 --> 01:02:16,799
That's it.

1647
01:02:16,866 --> 01:02:17,700
TO CAPTURE HER HEART!

1648
01:02:17,767 --> 01:02:21,037
-Yes, that's it. Crown daisy.
-Crown daisy.

1649
01:02:21,104 --> 01:02:22,805
Do you need someone to find them for you?

1650
01:02:22,872 --> 01:02:26,008
He can't help it. He's now getting older,

1651
01:02:26,075 --> 01:02:28,111
-so he can be forgetful.
-Yes, the grandfather-to-be.

1652
01:02:28,177 --> 01:02:29,679
HEY, YOU TOO?

1653
01:02:29,746 --> 01:02:31,080
INVESTED 1 MINUTE FOR THOSE!

1654
01:02:31,147 --> 01:02:32,315
He lost about a minute.

1655
01:02:32,381 --> 01:02:33,583
ROLLING

1656
01:02:34,083 --> 01:02:35,384
She's deep-frying something.

1657
01:02:35,451 --> 01:02:37,353
She's deep-frying the meatball.

1658
01:02:37,420 --> 01:02:41,624
Is Chef Eun-yeong
deep-frying the meatball?

1659
01:02:41,691 --> 01:02:42,992
Yes, I am.

1660
01:02:43,059 --> 01:02:44,761
-She's already deep-frying.
-She's deep-frying.

1661
01:02:44,827 --> 01:02:45,895
You have 11 minutes left.

1662
01:02:45,962 --> 01:02:46,963
Dang it.

1663
01:02:47,029 --> 01:02:49,065
-He said, "Dang it."
-Dang it.

1664
01:02:49,132 --> 01:02:52,435
-"Dang it"?
-He's blanching the crown daisy.

1665
01:02:52,502 --> 01:02:55,505
He almost forgot,
so he had to throw it in later.

1666
01:02:55,571 --> 01:02:57,573
That's why he used the water
inside the steamer.

1667
01:02:57,640 --> 01:02:58,508
It cooks quickly.

1668
01:02:59,075 --> 01:03:00,777
SALT, PEPPER

1669
01:03:01,344 --> 01:03:02,678
FOR VICTORY!

1670
01:03:03,246 --> 01:03:06,582
MY QUEEN HAS SPOKEN!

1671
01:03:07,450 --> 01:03:09,585
He squeezed the water out
and put it on the shrimp.

1672
01:03:09,652 --> 01:03:11,287
-And the wrap.
-That's so cool.

1673
01:03:11,354 --> 01:03:12,922
-Is he using plastic wrap?
-He's wrapping it.

1674
01:03:12,989 --> 01:03:14,323
-He'll steam that.
-It's a meatball.

1675
01:03:14,390 --> 01:03:15,358
He's making a shape.

1676
01:03:15,424 --> 01:03:16,392
Huh?

1677
01:03:16,459 --> 01:03:17,994
That's Chef Jong-won's move.

1678
01:03:18,060 --> 01:03:20,563
ANOTHER HOMAGE?

1679
01:03:21,264 --> 01:03:24,700
HE TURNED AN AVOCADO
INTO A LOLLIPOP

1680
01:03:25,401 --> 01:03:27,436
AND TIED THE KNOT
WITH HIS MOUTH

1681
01:03:27,737 --> 01:03:30,006
THE GOOD VIBES TECHNIQUE!

1682
01:03:30,640 --> 01:03:32,074
Everything is copied.

1683
01:03:32,141 --> 01:03:35,144
THE OLD VIBES TECHNIQUE!

1684
01:03:37,079 --> 01:03:40,750
I WANT TO BE BUZZWORTHY NO. 1 TOO!

1685
01:03:41,284 --> 01:03:43,386
THE SALT HUMAN IS AMBITIOUS!

1686
01:03:45,154 --> 01:03:46,489
That's not how you do it.

1687
01:03:46,556 --> 01:03:48,291
-That's not it.
-He's just eating the plastic.

1688
01:03:48,357 --> 01:03:50,459
-It should've been a string.
-He doesn't have it.

1689
01:03:50,526 --> 01:03:52,895
-He bit the plastic.
-It's not the plastic, but the string.

1690
01:03:52,962 --> 01:03:55,631
-He wants more buzz.
-He's trying to make a shape.

1691
01:03:55,698 --> 01:03:58,868
-And he'll steam it like that?
-That's how he'll steam it.

1692
01:03:58,935 --> 01:04:00,636
-He's going to steam it.
-He is.

1693
01:04:00,703 --> 01:04:02,271
That's a clever method.

1694
01:04:02,338 --> 01:04:06,876
The foil will keep it together
without making it burst.

1695
01:04:06,943 --> 01:04:08,678
-It'll cut down on the time.
-Yes.

1696
01:04:08,744 --> 01:04:10,246
He puts it into a steamer.

1697
01:04:10,546 --> 01:04:12,415
EUN-YEONG PREPS THE VEGGIES

1698
01:04:12,481 --> 01:04:14,417
SHIITAKE

1699
01:04:14,483 --> 01:04:16,419
GREEN ONION

1700
01:04:16,485 --> 01:04:19,088
-Peperoncino?
-Peperoncino.

1701
01:04:19,789 --> 01:04:22,024
4. STIR-FRY SHIITAKE
WITH SOY SAUCE AND SUGAR

1702
01:04:22,091 --> 01:04:23,092
Where did the time go?

1703
01:04:23,159 --> 01:04:25,161
Chef Eun-yeong seasoned
shiitake with soy sauce.

1704
01:04:25,228 --> 01:04:27,230
-That looks good.
-It must be.

1705
01:04:27,296 --> 01:04:29,832
She seasoned the shiitake
and stir-fried it.

1706
01:04:29,899 --> 01:04:31,300
-You have nine minutes left.
-Nine?

1707
01:04:31,367 --> 01:04:32,969
Time flies.

1708
01:04:33,769 --> 01:04:35,338
BUTTER

1709
01:04:35,905 --> 01:04:38,941
A FIRE BREAKS OUT

1710
01:04:39,008 --> 01:04:40,676
-Put it out! What's wrong?
-It's on fire!

1711
01:04:40,743 --> 01:04:42,545
THIS IS EXACTLY WHAT I WANTED…

1712
01:04:42,612 --> 01:04:44,881
THE TOP RANK IN FIREWORTHINESS!

1713
01:04:44,947 --> 01:04:46,515
-That's scary.
-Can someone put it out?

1714
01:04:47,183 --> 01:04:49,185
Are you copying me again?

1715
01:04:49,252 --> 01:04:50,953
Stop taking my moves!

1716
01:04:51,020 --> 01:04:55,291
Anyone can tell that he's taking
many moves from Webtoon Artist Poong…

1717
01:04:55,358 --> 01:04:57,960
-That's brown butter.
-…the second-most buzzworthy man.

1718
01:04:59,295 --> 01:05:00,529
THE THIRD BATCH OF SHRIMP

1719
01:05:00,596 --> 01:05:01,831
-Perilla leaves.
-Perilla leaves.

1720
01:05:01,898 --> 01:05:03,532
-Perilla leaves.
-Perilla leaves.

1721
01:05:03,599 --> 01:05:04,567
Olive oil.

1722
01:05:04,634 --> 01:05:06,936
He's probably making
perilla leaf pesto or oil.

1723
01:05:07,003 --> 01:05:08,237
Will you grind that?

1724
01:05:08,304 --> 01:05:10,006
THE 2ND FIRE

1725
01:05:10,072 --> 01:05:12,241
-It's a fire show. But it's too big.
-It's too big.

1726
01:05:12,308 --> 01:05:14,110
No, he's adding smokiness.

1727
01:05:14,176 --> 01:05:17,046
That was a huge fire. Is that okay?

1728
01:05:17,113 --> 01:05:18,614
Milk.

1729
01:05:18,681 --> 01:05:20,683
He's adding milk.

1730
01:05:22,752 --> 01:05:24,053
Man. Wait a moment.

1731
01:05:24,754 --> 01:05:26,355
MOVING IT INTO A PAN?

1732
01:05:26,422 --> 01:05:28,791
-Something seems ominous.
-He's spilling everything.

1733
01:05:28,858 --> 01:05:31,327
He must've run out of energy
after the crown daisy run.

1734
01:05:32,061 --> 01:05:34,297
-He can usually explain himself.
-Doing okay, Chef Hyun-suk?

1735
01:05:34,363 --> 01:05:35,431
I'm fine.

1736
01:05:35,998 --> 01:05:37,366
TOO CLOSE
NOT OKAY FOR EUN-YEONG…

1737
01:05:37,433 --> 01:05:39,902
-He's right next to Eun-yeong.
-He's speechless.

1738
01:05:39,969 --> 01:05:41,704
This is so nerve-racking.

1739
01:05:41,771 --> 01:05:44,006
-I can't watch.
-You can relax. No need to worry.

1740
01:05:44,073 --> 01:05:48,444
It seems like
things aren't going well for Hyun-suk.

1741
01:05:48,511 --> 01:05:52,882
-He never rushes like this, but today…
-No.

1742
01:05:52,949 --> 01:05:55,484
-He's on edge.
-The roux.

1743
01:05:55,551 --> 01:05:57,320
He must've gotten something mixed up.

1744
01:05:57,386 --> 01:06:01,424
You can easily become dazed
when you realize you forget an ingredient.

1745
01:06:01,490 --> 01:06:04,493
-He should've made the roux first.
-That's why 15 minutes are rough.

1746
01:06:04,560 --> 01:06:06,662
-It's an emergency.
-Was he trying to make roux?

1747
01:06:06,729 --> 01:06:09,532
He should've done that first,
but he got the steps switched.

1748
01:06:09,598 --> 01:06:12,068
I see. He should've made the roux first.

1749
01:06:12,134 --> 01:06:13,602
The steps are out of order.

1750
01:06:13,669 --> 01:06:16,439
Hyun-suk rarely makes these mistakes.

1751
01:06:16,505 --> 01:06:18,207
He doesn't.

1752
01:06:18,274 --> 01:06:20,109
-Is Chef Hyun-suk…
-Wait, that much?

1753
01:06:20,176 --> 01:06:22,044
Isn't that just milk soup?

1754
01:06:22,111 --> 01:06:24,180
-Jeez.
-He needed to make the roux first.

1755
01:06:24,246 --> 01:06:25,681
Aren't we rowdy?

1756
01:06:25,748 --> 01:06:26,716
No, it's fun.

1757
01:06:26,782 --> 01:06:28,951
He made everything
before he made the roux?

1758
01:06:29,018 --> 01:06:31,454
Hyun-suk is back in his element.

1759
01:06:31,520 --> 01:06:33,189
He did this in that while.

1760
01:06:33,255 --> 01:06:35,891
-You have seven minutes.
-Seven minutes.

1761
01:06:35,958 --> 01:06:37,293
She grabs water parsley.

1762
01:06:37,360 --> 01:06:39,128
Eun-yeong uses water parsley.

1763
01:06:39,195 --> 01:06:40,029
A SPOON OF OIL

1764
01:06:40,596 --> 01:06:43,799
5. SEASON WATER PARSLEY
WITH SALT AND PEPPER, THEN STIR-FRY

1765
01:06:44,633 --> 01:06:46,435
6. MIX WATER, SOY SAUCE, SUGAR,
OYSTER SAUCE, VINEGAR

1766
01:06:46,502 --> 01:06:49,038
What sauce are you making, Chef Eun-yeong?

1767
01:06:49,105 --> 01:06:51,941
It's for the meatball.

1768
01:06:52,008 --> 01:06:53,275
A meatball dip?

1769
01:06:53,342 --> 01:06:54,677
That's a huge meatball.

1770
01:06:54,744 --> 01:06:56,012
Wow.

1771
01:06:56,078 --> 01:06:57,046
She's short on time.

1772
01:06:57,613 --> 01:06:58,848
She pulls the meatball out.

1773
01:06:58,914 --> 01:07:01,550
Eun-yeong gets the meatball
out of the oil.

1774
01:07:01,617 --> 01:07:04,520
-It looks pretty.
-It's big.

1775
01:07:04,587 --> 01:07:06,756
You're cooking for the Queen.

1776
01:07:06,822 --> 01:07:08,424
She's cutting the meatball.

1777
01:07:08,491 --> 01:07:11,694
-The cross-section.
-I hope it's cooked thoroughly.

1778
01:07:11,761 --> 01:07:13,429
IT'S UNDERCOOKED?

1779
01:07:14,530 --> 01:07:15,831
She did that on purpose.

1780
01:07:15,898 --> 01:07:16,732
Intentionally?

1781
01:07:16,799 --> 01:07:19,869
-She'll scoop out the inside.
-She'll scoop it out and cook it again.

1782
01:07:20,770 --> 01:07:21,871
I SEE

1783
01:07:21,937 --> 01:07:24,340
-Is that how it's done?
-That's how it's done.

1784
01:07:24,407 --> 01:07:25,875
Will she cook that again?

1785
01:07:25,941 --> 01:07:27,076
After she scoops that out.

1786
01:07:27,143 --> 01:07:29,278
-Is she going to add fillings?
-Yes.

1787
01:07:29,345 --> 01:07:31,380
It didn't have to be fully cooked.

1788
01:07:31,447 --> 01:07:32,982
She just needed that space.

1789
01:07:33,049 --> 01:07:36,685
-The mushroom pieces go in!
-The shiitake!

1790
01:07:36,752 --> 01:07:39,188
-That's amazing. I knew you could do it.
-Intentionally undercooked.

1791
01:07:39,255 --> 01:07:40,990
-What's next?
-Today is…

1792
01:07:41,057 --> 01:07:42,691
-She'll steam that now.
-Steam it?

1793
01:07:42,758 --> 01:07:44,126
-And an egg yolk.
-A yolk?

1794
01:07:44,193 --> 01:07:46,095
An egg yolk? That's impressive.

1795
01:07:46,162 --> 01:07:48,164
-Will you put the top on?
-Will the top go back on?

1796
01:07:48,230 --> 01:07:49,632
-She'll steam it.
-Steaming.

1797
01:07:49,698 --> 01:07:51,200
-She should.
-She's going to steam it.

1798
01:07:51,267 --> 01:07:52,835
This is a complicated process.

1799
01:07:52,902 --> 01:07:54,637
It seems like a dish a king would eat.

1800
01:07:54,703 --> 01:07:57,940
Is it okay to steam something
after you deep-fry it?

1801
01:07:58,007 --> 01:07:59,375
-Is it okay?
-Is it?

1802
01:07:59,975 --> 01:08:00,876
Five minutes.

1803
01:08:00,943 --> 01:08:02,344
-Is it okay?
-You're up, Jung-hwan!

1804
01:08:02,411 --> 01:08:04,013
-Go try it.
-It's been fried.

1805
01:08:04,080 --> 01:08:06,382
-It's okay. It'll become tender.
-What?

1806
01:08:06,449 --> 01:08:09,185
Come to think of it, fish cakes get boiled
after they're deep-fried.

1807
01:08:09,251 --> 01:08:11,554
It's like making fritter-<i>jjigae.</i>

1808
01:08:11,954 --> 01:08:14,190
ADDING SHRIMP CREAM INTO A BLENDER!

1809
01:08:15,091 --> 01:08:16,525
He's using a lot of milk.

1810
01:08:16,592 --> 01:08:18,994
8. ADD MILK TO THE SHRIMP CREAM
AND BLEND TO FINISH THE SAUCE

1811
01:08:19,595 --> 01:08:21,096
STRAINING IT

1812
01:08:22,965 --> 01:08:25,534
THEN BOILED AGAIN TO MAKE RICHER!

1813
01:08:25,601 --> 01:08:28,804
-What's he doing?
-He keeps blending something.

1814
01:08:28,871 --> 01:08:32,341
He's blending perilla leaf oil.

1815
01:08:32,408 --> 01:08:35,678
Is the oil ready? Yes, it is.

1816
01:08:35,744 --> 01:08:36,879
The perilla oil is ready.

1817
01:08:36,946 --> 01:08:38,247
An apple.

1818
01:08:38,314 --> 01:08:39,448
CHOPPING INTO BOAT SHAPES

1819
01:08:39,515 --> 01:08:40,950
He's chopping an apple.

1820
01:08:42,852 --> 01:08:44,553
Can you bring me lemon <i>cheong?</i>

1821
01:08:44,620 --> 01:08:47,456
Lemon. He needs lemon <i>cheong.</i>

1822
01:08:47,523 --> 01:08:48,390
-Lemon <i>cheong?</i>
-He needs it.

1823
01:08:48,457 --> 01:08:49,358
Lemon?

1824
01:08:49,425 --> 01:08:51,627
-Lemon <i>cheong?</i>
-He needs it.

1825
01:08:51,694 --> 01:08:53,629
-You need us to bring it?
-Lemon <i>cheong,</i> please.

1826
01:08:53,696 --> 01:08:56,398
He's making the chefs run errands.

1827
01:08:56,465 --> 01:08:57,466
Master!

1828
01:08:58,934 --> 01:09:00,102
Lemon <i>cheong?</i>

1829
01:09:01,270 --> 01:09:02,171
LEMON CHEONG

1830
01:09:02,238 --> 01:09:05,407
10. BOIL DOWN APPLES
IN LEMON CHEONG AND VINEGAR

1831
01:09:05,474 --> 01:09:06,542
I'm running out of time.

1832
01:09:07,877 --> 01:09:09,578
8. STIR-FRY VEGGIES AND MIX WITH SOY SAUCE

1833
01:09:09,645 --> 01:09:10,813
What's this sauce?

1834
01:09:10,880 --> 01:09:12,448
I'll serve it with the meatball.

1835
01:09:12,515 --> 01:09:14,316
-Will you pour this on it?
-Yes.

1836
01:09:14,383 --> 01:09:17,520
Chef Eun-yeong is making
the meatball sauce.

1837
01:09:17,586 --> 01:09:20,556
I hope both steamed dishes turn out well.

1838
01:09:21,023 --> 01:09:22,758
LET ME CHECK IF IT'S COOKED

1839
01:09:23,459 --> 01:09:25,294
-Wow!
-It looks great.

1840
01:09:25,361 --> 01:09:26,896
-That's amazing.
-Look at that.

1841
01:09:26,962 --> 01:09:28,831
Is that the egg yolk?

1842
01:09:28,898 --> 01:09:29,732
Is it cooked?

1843
01:09:29,932 --> 01:09:31,233
PROUD OF HER

1844
01:09:31,300 --> 01:09:32,268
It's cooked.

1845
01:09:33,269 --> 01:09:35,204
She's not going to top it with the lid.

1846
01:09:35,271 --> 01:09:36,872
It looks like

1847
01:09:36,939 --> 01:09:39,775
Eun-yeong's recipe is coming along well,
according to the recipe.

1848
01:09:39,842 --> 01:09:41,310
As for him,

1849
01:09:41,377 --> 01:09:43,812
he's just everywhere.

1850
01:09:43,879 --> 01:09:45,347
-He's everywhere?
-Yes.

1851
01:09:45,414 --> 01:09:48,150
-He's everywhere, here and there.
-She's absolutely correct.

1852
01:09:48,217 --> 01:09:50,419
But he's a man with experience.

1853
01:09:50,486 --> 01:09:52,688
-That's true.
-I'll have to try their dishes.

1854
01:09:52,755 --> 01:09:54,924
-You have two minutes!
-Two minutes!

1855
01:09:54,990 --> 01:09:56,859
-Only two minutes!
-A minute and 40 seconds!

1856
01:09:56,926 --> 01:09:59,061
Chef Hyun-suk must've let his guard down,

1857
01:09:59,128 --> 01:10:00,863
whereas Eun-yeong had been
waiting for this.

1858
01:10:00,930 --> 01:10:03,799
Things are going smoothly for her
just as she planned.

1859
01:10:03,866 --> 01:10:05,401
-You got this.
-Now, the meatball.

1860
01:10:05,467 --> 01:10:07,703
The meatball
of the meatball's head is out.

1861
01:10:07,770 --> 01:10:09,972
-The meatball's head?
-Lion's head.

1862
01:10:10,039 --> 01:10:12,041
Yes, the lion's head,
not the meatball's head.

1863
01:10:12,107 --> 01:10:13,943
-What's the meatball's head?
-Lion's head.

1864
01:10:14,009 --> 01:10:15,077
I'm out of it too.

1865
01:10:15,144 --> 01:10:16,412
She's adding starch.

1866
01:10:16,478 --> 01:10:19,648
She's making it thicker with starch.

1867
01:10:19,715 --> 01:10:21,917
-The shrimp cream sauce.
-All right.

1868
01:10:21,984 --> 01:10:24,887
-It's way too hot.
-That's too hot.

1869
01:10:24,954 --> 01:10:26,789
-It's too hot. It's hot.
-Be careful.

1870
01:10:26,855 --> 01:10:28,324
It'd be so bad if it weren't cooked.

1871
01:10:28,390 --> 01:10:30,059
No, shrimp cooks quickly.

1872
01:10:30,626 --> 01:10:31,994
Has it been cooked through?

1873
01:10:32,061 --> 01:10:34,463
-It looks a bit undercooked.
-It's fully cooked.

1874
01:10:34,530 --> 01:10:37,399
Is it? The shrimp is cooked.

1875
01:10:38,467 --> 01:10:40,536
My goodness. They only have 58 seconds.

1876
01:10:40,603 --> 01:10:43,072
-One minute left.
-One minute!

1877
01:10:43,138 --> 01:10:44,740
Fifty seconds.

1878
01:10:44,807 --> 01:10:47,276
-Finish up.
-You must finish up.

1879
01:10:47,343 --> 01:10:50,379
Chef Eun-yeong!
Oh, you'll put the sauce on the bottom,

1880
01:10:50,446 --> 01:10:54,116
-and then the lion's head.
-I get it.

1881
01:10:54,183 --> 01:10:56,785
-Hyun-suk, the athlete… Wait, no.
-Athlete?

1882
01:10:56,852 --> 01:10:59,021
Things are so hectic over here.

1883
01:11:00,322 --> 01:11:01,657
-What's he using?
-This.

1884
01:11:01,724 --> 01:11:03,492
-Brown butter.
-Brown butter?

1885
01:11:03,559 --> 01:11:05,628
-Let me try this sauce!
-Sure.

1886
01:11:05,694 --> 01:11:07,529
-The shrimp sauce.
-The shrimp cream sauce.

1887
01:11:07,596 --> 01:11:09,365
They have 30 seconds left.

1888
01:11:09,431 --> 01:11:11,500
The cream sauce!

1889
01:11:11,567 --> 01:11:13,936
Is it good enough for the Queen?

1890
01:11:14,803 --> 01:11:15,904
WORRIED

1891
01:11:16,605 --> 01:11:17,773
ANTICIPATION

1892
01:11:17,840 --> 01:11:19,208
Goodness.

1893
01:11:19,275 --> 01:11:21,076
The Queen will be pleased!

1894
01:11:21,143 --> 01:11:22,311
SUCCESSFULLY GUARDED HER APPETITE

1895
01:11:25,281 --> 01:11:27,316
-Chef Hyun-suk is done!
-Are you done?

1896
01:11:27,383 --> 01:11:29,184
-He's so cool.
-What about the sauce?

1897
01:11:29,251 --> 01:11:31,253
-Is that all?
-Aren't you going to serve the sauce?

1898
01:11:31,320 --> 01:11:32,721
What's wrong? Are you done?

1899
01:11:33,222 --> 01:11:34,923
Fifteen seconds.

1900
01:11:34,990 --> 01:11:36,392
He wants to be her bodyguard.

1901
01:11:36,458 --> 01:11:38,627
-Ten seconds.
-That's Hyun-suk.

1902
01:11:38,694 --> 01:11:40,996
He couldn't focus
because he was thinking of that.

1903
01:11:41,063 --> 01:11:42,898
-He was preparing that pose.
-Five.

1904
01:11:42,965 --> 01:11:44,867
-Four. Three.
-Look at that. It's huge.

1905
01:11:44,933 --> 01:11:47,102
-Two. One.
-Two. One.

1906
01:11:47,169 --> 01:11:48,237
Time's up!

1907
01:11:48,304 --> 01:11:49,938
-She's done.
-Time's up.

1908
01:11:50,673 --> 01:11:53,442
Goodness. The battle is fierce.

1909
01:11:53,509 --> 01:11:56,178
-They're so amazing.
-Oh, my.

1910
01:11:56,245 --> 01:12:00,749
And now, both dishes were finished
just for Young-ok.

1911
01:12:00,816 --> 01:12:03,986
It's even more nerve-racking
to watch this in person.

1912
01:12:04,053 --> 01:12:05,421
You're all amazing.

1913
01:12:05,487 --> 01:12:08,190
Why don't you try
Chef Hyun-suk's dish first?

1914
01:12:08,524 --> 01:12:10,025
SMOOTH SHRIMP CREAM SAUCE

1915
01:12:10,926 --> 01:12:14,697
BOUNCY TERRINE,
SIMMERED APPLE AND PERILLA OIL

1916
01:12:15,464 --> 01:12:18,767
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S
ALL BOW TO THE GRAND QUEEN SHRIMP

1917
01:12:18,834 --> 01:12:20,002
Your Royal Highness.

1918
01:12:20,069 --> 01:12:22,237
Please allow me to serve the dish.

1919
01:12:22,905 --> 01:12:25,240
THE BODYGUARD SOUNDS SERIOUS

1920
01:12:25,307 --> 01:12:27,376
-He's anxious.
-The bodyguard himself.

1921
01:12:27,943 --> 01:12:29,144
He's scared.

1922
01:12:29,211 --> 01:12:30,279
He's so anxious.

1923
01:12:30,346 --> 01:12:32,314
It looks like a peeled tangerine.

1924
01:12:32,381 --> 01:12:34,116
It does look like that.

1925
01:12:34,183 --> 01:12:35,517
Is that a peeled tangerine?

1926
01:12:35,584 --> 01:12:37,519
It's a peeled tangerine with kiwi pieces.

1927
01:12:37,586 --> 01:12:39,455
-Is this how I eat it?
-It's a fruit dish.

1928
01:12:39,521 --> 01:12:40,489
The shrimp cream sauce.

1929
01:12:40,556 --> 01:12:41,657
MOUTH-WATERING

1930
01:12:41,724 --> 01:12:44,827
Please cut it and have it with the sauce.

1931
01:12:45,861 --> 01:12:47,930
HIS VOCALS MAY GET BETTER
WHILE GUARDING HER

1932
01:12:47,996 --> 01:12:50,065
-The Grand Queen Dowager's dish.
-Is it cooked?

1933
01:12:50,132 --> 01:12:52,735
What's on the inside?

1934
01:12:52,801 --> 01:12:55,537
-He put some crown daisies inside.
-Crown daisy.

1935
01:12:55,604 --> 01:12:57,639
-Have everything together.
-I love all shellfish…

1936
01:12:57,706 --> 01:13:01,143
-Please use a spoon to get everything.
-…including king crabs and lobsters.

1937
01:13:01,210 --> 01:13:02,878
Your voice is reaching no one.

1938
01:13:02,945 --> 01:13:04,747
SWOOSH

1939
01:13:04,813 --> 01:13:06,515
Please be quiet while she dines.

1940
01:13:06,582 --> 01:13:08,684
-Please quiet down when she talks.
-She was talking.

1941
01:13:08,751 --> 01:13:09,885
Should she use a spoon?

1942
01:13:09,952 --> 01:13:12,654
-Yes, have the sauce with everything.
-Tell me about it. I should.

1943
01:13:12,721 --> 01:13:14,790
-Let's see.
-And then have the apple separately…

1944
01:13:14,857 --> 01:13:16,058
She got everything.

1945
01:13:16,692 --> 01:13:19,628
A BITE WITH A PRETTY PIECE OF APPLE

1946
01:13:20,129 --> 01:13:22,564
If you served it on the same dish,
she'll eat it all together.

1947
01:13:22,631 --> 01:13:23,832
You should've used another dish.

1948
01:13:23,899 --> 01:13:26,368
He requested that
she eat the apple separately,

1949
01:13:26,435 --> 01:13:28,003
but she ate everything together.

1950
01:13:30,639 --> 01:13:31,774
What's it like?

1951
01:13:32,908 --> 01:13:34,943
I don't know
why he put crown daisy in here.

1952
01:13:35,010 --> 01:13:37,579
It's already good without it.

1953
01:13:37,646 --> 01:13:39,248
Without the crown daisy.

1954
01:13:39,314 --> 01:13:42,818
She's saying
you didn't have to run to grab that.

1955
01:13:42,885 --> 01:13:45,554
It was a roundabout way of saying that.

1956
01:13:45,621 --> 01:13:48,757
Everything is tender,
so I wanted to add a crunch.

1957
01:13:49,224 --> 01:13:50,659
FEELING THE TEXTURE

1958
01:13:50,726 --> 01:13:54,196
But the flavor changes
as I continue to chew on the crown daisy.

1959
01:13:54,763 --> 01:13:56,465
-The texture.
-Yes, it hits later.

1960
01:13:56,532 --> 01:13:57,566
-Later.
-That's the intention.

1961
01:13:57,633 --> 01:13:59,835
I wanted to add a bit of variety,
Your Royal Highness.

1962
01:14:00,402 --> 01:14:03,038
The flavor changed while I chewed.

1963
01:14:03,105 --> 01:14:05,340
Let me try just the shrimp.

1964
01:14:05,407 --> 01:14:08,577
She tries just the shrimp
without the crown daisy.

1965
01:14:11,647 --> 01:14:13,849
It would be troublesome
if it's better without it.

1966
01:14:13,916 --> 01:14:15,918
I think it's a taste
that makes her close her eyes.

1967
01:14:15,984 --> 01:14:19,321
This is nice too.
It's savory and delicious.

1968
01:14:21,356 --> 01:14:24,560
It's a pass as a dish
for a queen who's over 90.

1969
01:14:25,294 --> 01:14:28,363
PERFECT FOR HER TASTE

1970
01:14:28,430 --> 01:14:31,333
-Try the apple separately.
-After the savory taste,

1971
01:14:31,400 --> 01:14:33,569
-a piece of apple.
-Refresh yourself before you go back.

1972
01:14:34,203 --> 01:14:36,138
What's on top of the apple?

1973
01:14:36,205 --> 01:14:38,073
-I poured perilla oil on it.
-Perilla leaf oil.

1974
01:14:38,140 --> 01:14:42,244
The aromas of apples and perilla leaves
mix very well, so I tried doing that.

1975
01:14:42,311 --> 01:14:44,112
The apple has a nice balance.

1976
01:14:44,179 --> 01:14:45,247
Is the balance nice?

1977
01:14:45,314 --> 01:14:49,051
I like taking a bite of the shrimp
and then a bite of the apple.

1978
01:14:49,117 --> 01:14:50,652
I feel like the Queen.

1979
01:14:52,287 --> 01:14:54,790
A PERFECT DISH THAT MADE HER A QUEEN

1980
01:14:54,857 --> 01:14:57,759
Next, Chef Eun-yeong's dish.

1981
01:14:58,327 --> 01:15:01,697
CRUNCHY YET SOFT BIG SHRIMP MEATBALL
IN SWEET SAUCE

1982
01:15:02,831 --> 01:15:06,368
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S MEATBALL QUEEN

1983
01:15:08,070 --> 01:15:09,705
You served it with water parsley, right?

1984
01:15:09,771 --> 01:15:12,641
This one looks beautiful.

1985
01:15:12,708 --> 01:15:13,542
How should she eat it?

1986
01:15:13,609 --> 01:15:17,579
-Is she nervous?
-Pop the yolk and have it with the sauce.

1987
01:15:17,646 --> 01:15:20,682
-So cut it and eat everything together?
-Yes.

1988
01:15:20,749 --> 01:15:21,850
-Is the yolk the sauce?
-Yes.

1989
01:15:21,917 --> 01:15:24,386
-No, pop it and mix it with the sauce.
-There it is.

1990
01:15:24,453 --> 01:15:25,754
The yolk sauce.

1991
01:15:25,821 --> 01:15:26,989
It didn't seem cooked.

1992
01:15:27,055 --> 01:15:28,323
You only cooked the top.

1993
01:15:28,390 --> 01:15:30,492
-She had it half-cooked on purpose.
-Half-cooked.

1994
01:15:31,760 --> 01:15:33,262
-Goodness.
-Yes, right.

1995
01:15:33,328 --> 01:15:35,531
I saw her filling this with shiitake.

1996
01:15:35,597 --> 01:15:39,735
-Shiitake.
-I'm looking forward to checking out

1997
01:15:39,801 --> 01:15:42,037
what that will taste like.

1998
01:15:42,104 --> 01:15:43,639
-The shiitake.
-I'll try it.

1999
01:15:44,206 --> 01:15:47,876
-A piece of water parsley.
-Water parsley.

2000
01:15:47,943 --> 01:15:50,145
-I should eat it together.
-She's enjoying this.

2001
01:15:50,212 --> 01:15:53,282
Goodness. Wait a second.
I'm better off with a spoon.

2002
01:15:53,348 --> 01:15:55,050
-Yes, you have a spoon there.
-Yes.

2003
01:15:55,117 --> 01:15:57,553
It's so difficult to eat.

2004
01:15:57,619 --> 01:15:59,922
I made the pieces too big. I'm sorry.

2005
01:15:59,988 --> 01:16:01,790
I just got too much water parsley.

2006
01:16:01,857 --> 01:16:02,991
This isn't good.

2007
01:16:03,058 --> 01:16:05,127
Gosh, this is hard.

2008
01:16:05,193 --> 01:16:07,462
-It's a bit difficult to eat.
-One moment.

2009
01:16:07,529 --> 01:16:10,265
-The bodyguard is looking happier.
-You should've cut it for her.

2010
01:16:10,332 --> 01:16:12,501
-No, it's okay.
-Your Highness, shall I cut it?

2011
01:16:14,002 --> 01:16:16,505
-She got everything.
-She got it.

2012
01:16:16,572 --> 01:16:17,539
I'll try everything here.

2013
01:16:17,606 --> 01:16:19,107
-It takes too much work.
-In one bite?

2014
01:16:19,174 --> 01:16:21,009
A BIG MOUTHFUL

2015
01:16:21,076 --> 01:16:22,210
She eats so well.

2016
01:16:23,645 --> 01:16:25,581
Water parsley and…

2017
01:16:26,682 --> 01:16:28,617
-Her face.
-Her eyes.

2018
01:16:28,684 --> 01:16:31,353
-Delicious?
-We can't tell what she means by this.

2019
01:16:31,420 --> 01:16:32,688
What does this mean?

2020
01:16:32,754 --> 01:16:34,156
HEART POUNDS
OH, MY GOSH?

2021
01:16:34,222 --> 01:16:36,792
-What was that sign?
-She nodded at Chef Eun-yeong.

2022
01:16:36,959 --> 01:16:38,894
ANXIOUS

2023
01:16:38,961 --> 01:16:41,630
The way I ate this
may not look so dignified,

2024
01:16:41,697 --> 01:16:43,899
but the dish is very classy.

2025
01:16:45,367 --> 01:16:46,768
The dish is classy.

2026
01:16:46,835 --> 01:16:47,703
Goodness.

2027
01:16:49,471 --> 01:16:51,673
QUICK SCAN

2028
01:16:52,541 --> 01:16:54,810
She glanced at her bodyguard.

2029
01:16:54,876 --> 01:16:58,747
Some sweet dishes are good,
while some aren't so good.

2030
01:16:58,814 --> 01:17:02,117
But the sweetness of this dish
is immaculate.

2031
01:17:03,051 --> 01:17:05,887
-Some are good, and some are bad.
-She found the right balance.

2032
01:17:06,455 --> 01:17:09,191
ANOTHER BIG BITE WITH THE SAUCE

2033
01:17:09,858 --> 01:17:10,859
Mmm.

2034
01:17:12,060 --> 01:17:12,928
Mmm.

2035
01:17:12,995 --> 01:17:13,862
-Goodness.
-Hmm?

2036
01:17:13,929 --> 01:17:14,763
Is it that amazing?

2037
01:17:14,830 --> 01:17:16,565
How did you make this sauce?

2038
01:17:16,632 --> 01:17:18,033
How did you make it?

2039
01:17:18,100 --> 01:17:20,268
You were curious about the shiitake.
What's that like?

2040
01:17:20,335 --> 01:17:22,070
-It's so good.
-The shiitake?

2041
01:17:22,137 --> 01:17:23,472
I'm speechless.

2042
01:17:23,705 --> 01:17:24,906
THE SPECTATORS ALSO BECOME HAPPY

2043
01:17:24,973 --> 01:17:27,776
She's speechless.
Goodness, this is bad news for him.

2044
01:17:27,843 --> 01:17:29,344
-Whatever.
-"Whatever"?

2045
01:17:29,411 --> 01:17:30,879
BOTH DISHES MADE THE QUEEN HAPPY

2046
01:17:30,946 --> 01:17:33,315
It's your time to choose.

2047
01:17:33,382 --> 01:17:35,183
The Queen must choose

2048
01:17:35,250 --> 01:17:37,419
one of the two chefs.

2049
01:17:37,486 --> 01:17:38,854
<i>Press one for Eun-yeong</i>

2050
01:17:39,588 --> 01:17:40,956
<i>and two for Hyun-suk.</i>

2051
01:17:41,790 --> 01:17:43,625
Please make your decision

2052
01:17:43,692 --> 01:17:45,293
and press the button!

2053
01:17:46,995 --> 01:17:48,263
It must be exhausting for the Queen.

2054
01:17:48,330 --> 01:17:50,599
-She pressed the button.
-It must be exhausting.

2055
01:17:50,666 --> 01:17:52,334
-It's a lot.
-She pushed it hard.

2056
01:17:52,401 --> 01:17:55,437
I wonder who the winner is.

2057
01:17:55,504 --> 01:17:58,373
Let's find out Young-ok's decision!

2058
01:17:58,440 --> 01:18:00,042
Show us!

2059
01:18:00,108 --> 01:18:01,343
The order was Queen's Dream,

2060
01:18:01,410 --> 01:18:03,545
a dish dedicated to the Queen.

2061
01:18:03,612 --> 01:18:05,847
Will Chef Hyun-suk win?

2062
01:18:05,914 --> 01:18:08,450
Or will Chef Eun-yeong

2063
01:18:08,517 --> 01:18:12,220
beat Hyun-suk and win a star?

2064
01:18:12,287 --> 01:18:13,889
Who did Young-ok choose?

2065
01:18:13,955 --> 01:18:15,457
Who is it?

2066
01:18:15,524 --> 01:18:16,825
Whose dish

2067
01:18:16,892 --> 01:18:19,461
humored the Queen's taste?

2068
01:18:21,463 --> 01:18:23,198
PARK EUN-YEONG WINS

2069
01:18:23,265 --> 01:18:24,933
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S MEATBALL QUEEN WINS

2070
01:18:25,000 --> 01:18:26,835
Chef Eun-yeong wins!

2071
01:18:26,902 --> 01:18:28,136
She's on fire.

2072
01:18:28,203 --> 01:18:30,972
PARK EUN-YEONG GETS HER REVENGE
AFTER THE CHAMPIONSHIP

2073
01:18:31,039 --> 01:18:34,776
If the Queen were to have
a special dish on her throne,

2074
01:18:34,843 --> 01:18:38,847
I would have Eun-yeong's dish
with this balanced sweetness.

2075
01:18:38,914 --> 01:18:40,649
It was very delicious.

2076
01:18:40,716 --> 01:18:43,452
-You had to choose her.
-I had to.

2077
01:18:43,518 --> 01:18:47,122
It would be nice
if you sold this at your restaurant.

2078
01:18:47,189 --> 01:18:49,224
-At her restaurant?
-Yes, there.

2079
01:18:49,291 --> 01:18:50,826
-At her workplace.
-I want to go and eat it.

2080
01:18:50,892 --> 01:18:52,661
-It was so good.
-You should do that for her.

2081
01:18:53,662 --> 01:18:55,197
COMPOSED

2082
01:18:55,263 --> 01:18:56,765
You could've been the champion

2083
01:18:56,832 --> 01:18:59,234
if you played only one round
against him last year.

2084
01:18:59,301 --> 01:19:01,069
Tell me about it. I could've won.

2085
01:19:01,136 --> 01:19:04,106
I would've seen a better result
if I played just one round.

2086
01:19:04,339 --> 01:19:05,707
THE REAL MADWOMAN IS SO DARING

2087
01:19:05,774 --> 01:19:07,909
-She's still disappointed from last year.
-Yes.

2088
01:19:07,976 --> 01:19:10,045
She said she would've won

2089
01:19:10,112 --> 01:19:13,014
if she played just one round against me.

2090
01:19:13,081 --> 01:19:15,650
So why didn't you rake in more wins?

2091
01:19:16,418 --> 01:19:19,254
-That's the ground, isn't it?
-You're bitter.

2092
01:19:19,321 --> 01:19:20,856
-Come on.
-Before the championship--

2093
01:19:20,922 --> 01:19:22,624
-She got to him.
-Don't be so twisted.

2094
01:19:22,691 --> 01:19:23,992
She got to him.

2095
01:19:24,059 --> 01:19:26,228
You're going to make
Young-ok uncomfortable.

2096
01:19:26,294 --> 01:19:27,395
-Come on.
-Come on.

2097
01:19:27,462 --> 01:19:28,697
DARN IT

2098
01:19:28,764 --> 01:19:30,665
Why do you only pick on me?

2099
01:19:30,732 --> 01:19:31,900
Everyone teased you.

2100
01:19:31,967 --> 01:19:33,869
The biggest flaw was this.

2101
01:19:33,935 --> 01:19:35,270
It was a bit too salty.

2102
01:19:35,337 --> 01:19:36,705
It was a bit too salty!

2103
01:19:36,772 --> 01:19:39,341
You kept sprinkling salt on it!

2104
01:19:39,407 --> 01:19:41,276
But first,
get your frozen shoulder treated.

2105
01:19:41,977 --> 01:19:43,345
This means

2106
01:19:43,411 --> 01:19:44,880
Eun-yeong wins against Hyun-suk

2107
01:19:44,946 --> 01:19:46,882
and takes the first star!

2108
01:19:46,948 --> 01:19:48,683
She's currently in first place.

2109
01:19:48,750 --> 01:19:50,986
-Great work.
-Your Royal Highness, please.

2110
01:19:51,052 --> 01:19:52,420
Do I have to give it to her too?

2111
01:19:52,487 --> 01:19:54,322
-I can't believe this.
-Thank you, Your Highness.

2112
01:19:54,389 --> 01:19:58,160
-So this is the spot.
-This is your second star, Eun-yeong.

2113
01:19:58,226 --> 01:20:01,196
-You have two.
-She's now in first place with two stars!

2114
01:20:01,263 --> 01:20:03,632
-Eun-yeong has two wins!
-I hope you continue to do well.

2115
01:20:03,698 --> 01:20:05,000
Congratulations.

2116
01:20:05,066 --> 01:20:07,002
Eun-yeong even takes Hyun-suk down!

2117
01:20:07,068 --> 01:20:09,171
Just sitting here makes my heart race.

2118
01:20:09,237 --> 01:20:11,139
From the side, his eyes remind me

2119
01:20:11,206 --> 01:20:12,707
of a vast lake.

2120
01:20:14,109 --> 01:20:16,478
The colors are bewitching.

2121
01:20:16,545 --> 01:20:18,613
She's so into him.

2122
01:20:18,680 --> 01:20:19,948
<i>He's the target of my jealousy.</i>

2123
01:20:20,015 --> 01:20:21,716
I will steal his popularity and followers.

2124
01:20:21,783 --> 01:20:22,617
The spinning.

2125
01:20:22,684 --> 01:20:24,586
He's so cool!

2126
01:20:24,653 --> 01:20:25,620
Really? That's cool?

2127
01:20:25,687 --> 01:20:26,621
Is he copying Jong-won?

2128
01:20:26,688 --> 01:20:28,623
Cut it out! I mean it. Stop it!

2129
01:20:28,690 --> 01:20:29,724
-What is this?
-What are you doing?

2130
01:20:29,791 --> 01:20:30,959
How do you do this?

2131
01:20:31,026 --> 01:20:32,561
That's not a technique for everyone.

2132
01:20:32,627 --> 01:20:34,462
<i>Today, I'll ram into him like a wild boar.</i>

2133
01:20:34,529 --> 01:20:35,797
<i>He must overcome his Poongphobia.</i>

2134
01:20:35,864 --> 01:20:37,365
I absolutely have to win today.

2135
01:20:37,432 --> 01:20:38,533
Poong, I need tongs.

2136
01:20:38,600 --> 01:20:39,634
A SUCCESSFUL DIVERSION

2137
01:20:39,701 --> 01:20:40,902
Hey! You can't take my tongs!

2138
01:20:40,969 --> 01:20:41,837
LOST HIS TONGS

2139
01:20:41,903 --> 01:20:43,538
What is Webtoon Artist Poong making?

2140
01:20:43,605 --> 01:20:44,639
This isn't going to work.

2141
01:20:44,706 --> 01:20:45,774
That's odd.

2142
01:20:45,841 --> 01:20:47,409
-Hmm?
-Wait.

2143
01:20:47,475 --> 01:20:48,443
It's so good.

2144
01:20:48,510 --> 01:20:49,411
HOW IS IT GOOD?

2145
01:20:49,477 --> 01:20:50,445
-Please!
-Really?

2146
01:20:50,512 --> 01:20:51,580
WILL HE OVERCOME HIS POONGPHOBIA?

2147
01:20:51,646 --> 01:20:52,647
<i>It's an emergency.</i>

2148
01:20:55,317 --> 01:20:57,118
-It's good. Wait a minute.
-Yes, it's good.

2149
01:20:57,185 --> 01:20:59,321
Poong, why do you always do so well
against Nam-no?

2150
01:21:09,197 --> 01:21:14,202
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
